title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine both dressings well.
Place all vegetables in a large bowl and pour dressing mix over them. Toss gently to coat. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours, stirring several times.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cover wild rice with water and microwave on High for 6 minutes. Drain and repeat.
Brown meat, mix with other ingredients and add to rice.
Cover with wax paper or casserole cover and microwave on High for 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Let stand for 4 minutes.

title: zucchini ground beef italian
directions: In olive oil, saute onions, green pepper and garlic together for 2 minutes.
Stir in ground beef.
Cook until browned.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick made meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into loaf.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.
The
last 5 to 10 minutes you can cover it with a sauce of:

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix together.
Shape into balls.
Pan-fry in skillet until brown.
Place in baking pan to keep warm after cooking in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: old-fashioned raisin bars
directions: Combine raisins and water; bring to boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in oil, sugar and egg.
Sift together dry ingredients; beat into raisin mixture.
Pour into greased cake pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, salt and milk until mixture becomes a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Stir until thickened.
Pour into buttered pan. Cut into squares.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cool chicken and set aside.
Cook noodles in broth from chicken.
Cook until almost done.
Add other ingredients, along with chicken.
Cook until done.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix in blender, then you have sweetened condensed milk.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl for 15 minutes.
Pour in cake pan and bake 30 minutes or until top is light brown.
After it cools, turn on aluminum foil to take cake out.
Turn cake again so it is up right.
Then add chocolate frosting.

title: devil's food cake(you will feel naughty when eating this cake.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix brown sugar, sugar, vegetable oil, salt and flour to form a crumbly mixture.
Set aside 1 cup of this for cake topping.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg with the buttermilk, then add to large mixture.
Stir in baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg, and mix well.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a casserole dish.
Top with mixture of 1 cup Ritz cracker crumbs, 1/2 stick melted oleo and 1/2 cup slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated pot roast
directions: Roll roast in flour and brown in margarine until dark brown. Add all ingredients.
Cook on top of stove until tender or about 3-4 hours according to thickness of roast.

title: cheese-garlic bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Spread onto Boboli bread and broil until bubbly.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Mix gradually in different bowl:
margarine, peanut butter, brown sugar, white sugar and eggs.
Put in dry ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes in a greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Frost.

title: bonnie rayburn's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Shape mixture into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2 loaf pan.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine into cake mix as if for pie dough.
Mix in coconut.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan; pat down.
Build up edges.
Bake for 10 minutes and remove from oven. Spread pie filling over crust.
Mix sour cream and eggs well and drizzle over the top.
Bake for 25 minutes more.
Good warm or cold.

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Brown the bacon.
Set aside and brown ground beef and onion. In a large casserole, mix the last five ingredients.
Add meat and onion mixture and mix well.
Add the beans.
If pork and beans have a lot of liquid, drain some off.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach lasagna rolls
directions: Cook spinach and lasagna noodles separately according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.

title: walnut torte
directions: Beat egg whites and baking powder until stiff.
Crush crackers and fold into egg whites.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Will be a light golden brown and firm.
Cool and cut.
(Better when made the day before.) Serve with whipped cream on top or Cool Whip.

title: turnip greens
directions: Wash greens well to remove dirt; rinse at least 3 times in an abundance of water.
Put small leaves in pot and strip larger leaves from stems.
Before adding to pot container, put in 1 quart of cold water; cut salt pork into strips about one-inch thick and drop into pot.
Add Crisco or lard.
Cover pot and bring to a boil. Periodically stir greens in pot so as to allow those on top to go to the bottom.
Then push down so leaves are covered with water.
Lower heat and boil slowly for 2 hours (the longer the better), adding water to keep greens covered.
Actual cooking time depends on tenderness of greens.
Juice from greens is good served over cornbread and with pepper sauce on them.

title: pineapple cream cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well; refrigerate.
Serve on date nut or whole wheat bread.
Yields 1 cup.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Pour beans in casserole.
Add mushroom soup.
Cover with onion slices.
Cook in 350° oven until onion slices are done.

title: lamingtons(an australian treat)
directions: Make cake in 13 x 9-inch tin.
Let cool and cut into 2-inch squares.
Make chocolate frosting, making it thinner than normal; very runny is best.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Drop chicken into boiling water 5 to 8 minutes.
Debone it (or start with boneless and save the trouble!)
Spray an oblong 9 x 13-inch casserole with nonstick spray.
Line pan with chicken breasts.
Combine a jar of sauce with cut up onions and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Top breasts with sliced cheese (cover completely!) Pour sauce over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
It's done when cheese bubbles!

title: non-fried frittata
directions: Beat eggs.
Add salt, pepper, Parmesan and vegetables.
Pour batter into a round 9-inch oiled pan or 9 x 9-inch square pan. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with parsley.

title: gumdrop bars
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and water. Stir.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Stir in gumdrops.
Spread on a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until center springs back when pushed.

title: freddie's sweet potatoes
directions: In square baking pan, melt margarine or butter.
Sprinkle light brown sugar to cover bottom of pan.
Peel sweet potatoes and cut each into 3 lengthwise pieces and lay into bottom of pan. Sprinkle pumpkin pie spice or cinnamon on top of sweet potatoes to cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus tuna pecan salad with water chestnuts
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well to evenly distribute and coat well with mayonnaise.
Add seasoning to taste.
If salad is dry, add a bit more mayonnaise.
Serve as a sandwich or as a salad on a bed of lettuce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab and pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until done in salted water.
When done, rinse in cold water, drain and cool.
Make sure there are no shells in the crab and that it is well drained.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
This makes a lot, but is easy to cut in half.

title: individual quick cheese cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Put cupcake papers in muffin pans.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in each.
Fill cups 3/4 full of cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and top with pie filling.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape mixture into cocktail size balls. Heat oil.
Brown and cook meatballs.
Keep warm.
Pour off fat.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix shortening with flour until crumbly.
Add buttermilk, a little at a time, until you can form a soft dough (a little less than one cup).
Place dough on lightly floured surface; pat or roll dough out until smooth and about 3/4-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits with biscuit cutter.
Place on a buttered cookie sheet. Brush top with milk.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: quickie dessert
directions: Place 1 quart rhubarb and enough sugar to taste in bottom of baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, pinch salt, and egg, and spread over fruit.
Bake at 350 degrees.
Any kind of fruit can be used instead of rhubarb.

title: crumbed mushrooms
directions: Choose small mushrooms about the same size.
Wash and trim off hard end of stems.
Peel onion, chop finely, and saute in 1/2 ounce butter until transparent.
Add whole mushrooms, salt, pepper and dry sherry; simmer gently 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain and cool. Dip in beaten egg, roll in bread crumbs and fry quickly in remaining hot butter until crisp and golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: bread pudding
directions: In a well-greased casserole dish, mix milk and bread crumbs together.
Soak 5 minutes.
Stir in margarine, both sugars and salt.
Beat eggs well and add to mixture.
Stir in vanilla and raisins.
Set casserole in a pan of water.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Test with knife in the center.
When done, drizzle on a powdered sugar glaze or serve plain.

title: chocolate chocolate chip fruit tart(makes one 9-inch tart)
directions: Press cookie dough evenly into bottom and up side of greased 9-inch fluted tart pan with removable bottom.* Bake in preheated 350° oven for 18 to 22 minutes or until edge is set and center is still slightly soft.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in small mixer bowl until smooth. Spread evenly over cooled cookie crust to within 1/2-inch of edge; arrange fruit as desired.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Remove rim of pan; slice into wedges.

title: sparkling fruit punch
directions: Stir all ingredients together and keep chilled.

title: german potato salad
directions: Mix bacon and other ingredients except for potatoes in bacon drippings. Cook for a few minutes. Pour over sliced potatoes in baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. This is good reheated also.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: In a heavy iron skillet, melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together, beating eggs and adding last.
Pour mixture into the hot pan of butter; stir until heated.
Put skillet into a 325° oven to bake.
When crusted around the edge and top, turn under and let the crust form again. Do this twice, allowing the last to remain on sides and top.
Time required to bake is 40 minutes.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix oil with sugar and beat well.
Then add all dry ingredients and beat.
Add carrots and nuts.
Last, add one egg at a time and beat well.
Bake 45 minutes in moderate oven for 1 loaf.

title: antipasto dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: cauliflower egyptian style
directions: Separate, and clean buds, drop in boiling salted water for 5 minutes, remove from water.
Chop onions and brown in butter.
Add tomato paste to browned onions.
Beat eggs, dip cauliflower in beaten eggs and brown in butter slightly.
Pour tomato paste and onions over cauliflower.
Cover and steam in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch spectacular
directions: For crust:
Mix flour, margarine and 1/4 cup pecan pieces and press into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: filbert banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs; beat well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix with chopped filberts. Combine mashed bananas and milk.
Add the liquid alternately with the dry ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hot mocha mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in container with lid.
To mix, add 2 heaping tablespoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: tortilla turnovers
directions: Brown ground meat, mashed up.
Drain off fat.
Add seasoning mix and 3/4 cup water.
Bring to simmer, cook until most of liquid is absorbed.
Place tortillas on ungreased baking sheets.
In center of each, place a portion of meat mixture.
Sprinkle meat with cheese, onion and salsa.
Bake at 500° just until cheese melts, this just takes a minute or so.
Remove from oven and fold over, melted cheese will seal turnover.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cook in double boiler on medium heat until reaches desired thickness.
Excellent on ham. Will keep indefinitely if refrigerated.
Also makes a great pretzel dip.

title: spice bars
directions: In a saucepan, mix first five ingredients and bring to a boil; let cool.
In a bowl, mix flour, baking soda and spices.
Combine the cooled raisin mixture with the flour mixture and add the dates and nuts.
Spread on a greased 13 x 9-inch cookie sheet and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still warm.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix and pour on cake.

title: maryland spoon bread
directions: Put cornmeal, drippings, sugar and salt into baking dish. Pour the boiling water over them gradually and beat well.
When the mixture is cool, add the beaten egg, milk, soda and 1 teaspoon cold water. Beat the whole mixture well.
Bake in a deep dish 20 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: no bake cheese pie
directions: For crust, combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine and sugar. With the back of a spoon, press into a 9 x 13-inch or an 8 x 12-inch pan.
With a mixer, blend cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk.
Add lemon juice.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over crust.
Top with can of pie filling.
Chill for several hours before cutting.

title: banana punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Mix all the above ingredients together with sugar and water mixture.
Cool and freeze.
Thaw 3 hours prior to serving.
Put in punch bowl and pour ginger ale over it.
Serves 50.

title: salad dressing for sweet coleslaw
directions: Cook, stirring constantly, on medium heat to desired thickness.

title: tomato crabmeat aspic
directions: Heat tomato juice with onion, bay leaf and celery; strain and add gelatin, softened in cold water.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add beef consomme, lemon juice and seasonings.
Cool until partially set.
Add crabmeat and sliced olives.
Chill until firm in individual molds.
Unmold on lettuce; serve with mayonnaise.
If desired, make in oblong mold and cut in squares. Makes 6 servings.

title: french toast waffles
directions: Combine eggs, milk, melted butter, 10x sugar and salt.
Beat thoroughly.
Add grated lemon rind.
Cut slices of bread to fit waffle iron.
Coat bread well in butter and toast slices on hot waffle iron.
Serve immediately with warm maple syrup, honey or cinnamon sugar mixture.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar. Add vegetable oil, eggs, water, pumpkin and nuts.
Mix only until blended.
Bake in 3 well-greased pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool at least 5 minutes in pans.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn. Mix all ingredients in medium bowl. Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: squash dressing
directions: Chop onion and cook in oleo until onions look clear. Mash squash with fork. Combine onion and cream of chicken soup. Beat eggs and add bread crumbs. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook like you would chicken and dressing.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Cream 3 Tbsp. sugar with 1-1/2 sticks of margarine.
Stir in 2 c. of coarsely crushed pretzels.
Press this mixture into a 13x9 pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs for 5 minutes or beat until thick. Sift flour, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to mixture.
Also, add apples and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: savory sausage and lentil stew
directions: Sift through and rinse lentils, picking out any stones or shriveled lentils.
Place in oven with water and seasoning. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 35 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cut pimiento, green pepper and mushrooms fine.
Use as much as suits your taste.
Put a layer of corn flakes in a buttered casserole.
Then, add a layer of tuna, green pepper, pimiento, mushrooms, corn flakes, crumbled potato chips, white sauce and mushroom soup.
Repeat until all the ingredients have been used. Put a layer of crumbled potato chips over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not add any salt.
(I use Empress brand tuna; it is packed in water, which I pour off.)

title: congealed ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Place juice in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add jello stirring until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add sherbet; stir until sherbet is melted.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Add pineapple and 1/2 of the oranges.
Spoon into 6 oiled cups or a mold.
Cover and chill until firm.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Combine butter and garlic.
Set aside.
Combine breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir to blend.
Dip each chicken breast in butter mixture and coat each breast with breadcrumb mixture.
Roll tightly, starting with narrow end. Secure with wooden toothpick.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly with beater, then beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until a knife inserted 1-inch from side of filling comes out clean.
The center may look a bit soft but will set later.

title: garlic bubble
directions: Mix and melt in saucepan.
Slightly thaw 2 loaves of frozen bread dough.
Cut into 16 pieces per loaf.
Cut 32 cubes of Velveeta.
Wrap dough around cheese and dip into butter sauce. Put balls into buttered Bundt pan and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add salt, then flour and milk. Mix gently.
Add dates, nuts, candy and coconut to batter.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 250° in a large tube pan.

title: tomato crouton salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toss bread cubes with olive oil, thyme, salt and pepper.
Place in single layer on a baking sheet; toast for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden.
Remove and cool; reserve. Place tomatoes in a large serving bowl.
Peel, halve lengthwise and seed cucumbers.
Cut in 1-inch lengths.
Add to tomatoes, along with shallots, parsley, extra virgin olive oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Just before serving, add toasted bread cubes; toss thoroughly.
Divide arugula between serving plates; top with salad.

title: pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: unbaked chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk for 4 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: banana breeze
directions: Melt margarine, sugar and cinnamon in small pan.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly until bubbles form around edges of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add corn flake crumbs, mix well.
Press mixture evenly in 9-inch pie pan to form crust.
Chill.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop the popcorn; salt to taste.
Combine sugar, syrup and Jell-O in saucepan; bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat. Pour over popcorn.
Form into balls.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add raisins, chopped walnuts, melted butter or margarine and applesauce.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch or 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with butter icing.
Sprinkle with shredded orange rind.
Decorate with walnut halves.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Crush cookies.
Press 1/2 cookies into 9 x 13 dish.
Beat eggs and sugar till stiff and fluffy (10 to 15 minutes).
Add lemon juice and strawberries.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.
Freeze.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large pot, simmer chicken, celery, carrot, onion, peppercorns and seasoned salt in water until chicken falls apart. Remove chicken from pot.
Let cool, then skin, bone and tear into pieces.
Set aside.
Remove vegetables from broth, pressing as much of the liquid from vegetables as possible.
Bring broth to a boil.
Cook noodles in boiling broth 6 minutes.
Add bouillon cubes, stirring to mix well.
Stir in undiluted cream of chicken soup.
Stir gently to dissolve lumps, but try not to break noodles too much.
Stir in chicken pieces.
Add parsley flakes, red pepper flakes (if desired), minced onion, pepper and additional salt if desired.
Heat through.
Serve to hungry crowd with lots of hot buttered cornbread.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and egg yolks.
Add just enough milk to mix good, then add rest of ingredients.
Add coconut when taken off the stove.
Put meringue on top.
Sprinkle some coconut on top of meringue.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil well.
Beat in eggs.
Add pumpkin, dry ingredients and water alternately.
Stir in nuts last.
Bake 1 hour in prepared loaf pans at 375°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: imperial crab casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Mix first 8 ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Mix 2 tablespoons mayonnaise with milk.
Pour on top. Sprinkle with paprika lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Crust:
Boil margarine and water.
Turn off heat.
Add flour. Beat until it forms a ball.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
This will raise in spots and look funny.
Cool; it will fall.

title: modified rice pilaf
directions: Saute
onions, mushrooms and garlic in butter or margarine. Combine with cooked rice.

title: haystacks
directions: Cut lettuce and tomatoes to desired size (bite size is best). Heat chili beans.
Once you have done this, you can begin serving Haystacks.

title: pie crust
directions: Set aside 1/3 of flour; combine remaining flour with salt.
Add Crisco 1/3 at a time.
Pour water over mixture and press together making a ball; set 10 minutes.
Roll to make two 9-inch pie crusts.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix together.
Roll out mixture.
Cut into strips, then boil until done.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Combine mayonnaise, vegetable oil, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper and mix with a wire whisk.	Pour over broccoli and cauliflower and let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: fruit punch(light and refreshing)
directions: Pour fruit juice over ice ring in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Garnish with orange slices, strawberries and mint leaves.
Serves 25.

title: john's bar cookies
directions: Mix 1 cup butter, sugars and egg yolks.
Add flour and oats. Spread in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Melt Hershey bars with 2 tablespoons butter.
Spread over cooled cookie layer.
Sprinkle with nuts and cut into bars.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook hamburger and onion. Drain. Add tomato paste, water, chili powder, salt and pepper. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake with pineapple, coconut and walnuts
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil rapidly for 5 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Puree strawberries in blender or food processor, leaving small chunks of berries.
Add pureed strawberries and lemon and orange juices to the sugar-water and mix thoroughly.
Pour into freezer trays or containers to freeze firm.
Do not pour into dessert glasses to freeze as glass might break.
Makes about 3 cups of 6 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with the coconut. Sprinkle the pecans over the coconut.
Mix cake mix as directed. Spread over the pecans and coconut. Mix the cream cheese with the oleo and powdered sugar.
Mix well. Spoon mixture on top of cake mix. Bake at 350° for approximately 55 minutes. Cool and cut in squares.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder, sugar and milk.
Melt butter in pan.
Pour flour mixture in pan.
Pour on peaches; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: mushrooms in sour cream
directions: Prepare in chafing dish.
Wash, trim and slice mushrooms. Saute in butter over moderate heat in a covered pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Season with salt, pepper, oregano, nutmeg and lemon juice.
Toast French bread.
Reheat mushrooms in chafing dish.
Add sour cream, stirring while it heats.
Do not boil; cream will separate.
Serve on bread.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Cook stuffing mix per package directions.
Set aside to cool. Mix meat with crumbs and spices.
Put half the meat on bottom of loaf pan.
Make an indentation in the middle.
Put stuffing mix in. Place other half of meat on top, sealing the sides with water. Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.
Let sit before slicing.
Also good cold.
Serves 6.

title: green tomato bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour the bottom and 1/2 inch up the sides of two 8 x 4 x 2 inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl stir together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and soda.
Combine eggs, oil, vanilla, chopped green tomatoes.
Add egg mixture all at once to dry mixture.
Stir until moistened. Batter will be lumpy.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55-60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant
until tender.
Mix all together and bake in greased casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add grated sharp cheese and put back into oven until melted.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions and bake. When cake is done, immediately poke holes in the cake and pour Eagle Brand milk over the top, making sure entire cake is covered. Pour chocolate syrup over Eagle Brand milk layer. Let cake cool for 10 minutes then place in refrigerator. When cake has cooled completely, spread Cool Whip over the top and sprinkle with crushed Butterfingers.

title: onion rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry tunnel cream cake
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and food coloring.
Stir in strawberries.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping; fill cake hole with mixture.
Chill 3 hours.
Frost with remaining topping.
Put whole strawberries on top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together in bowl; season to taste.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour in bottom of pie shell.
Add mixture.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until top crust is brown.
Use ready-made pie shell (top and bottom).

title: french toast
directions: Preheat griddle to 350°. Mix eggs, milk, vanilla, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together. Dip bread in mixture. Cook on griddle. Cook until both sides are light brown. After you remove the bread, sprinkle both sides with sifted powdered sugar. No syrup needed.

title: elizabeth ann cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add brown and white sugar, creaming well. Sift flour and baking powder together.
Stir soda in cup of sour milk.
Add flour and milk alternately to creamed butter and sugar. Add unbeaten eggs.
Beat well.
Add nuts, coconut, vanilla, raisins and grape juice.
Bake in 4 small layers or 3 large ones.

title: fat-free green beans and potatoes
directions: All ingredients are variable according to individual taste.

title: fettuccine with tuna sauce
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, prepare fettuccine as label directs.

title: sugar-free spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients. Store in a tightly covered container.

title: merlot roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. The amounts on this are close. You can adjust according to your taste. Coat your roast in the flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder and then lightly brown both sides in oil.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together, adding small amount of salt and 2 teaspoons cayenne pepper.
Top with fresh parsley.
Use with loaf of pumpernickel bread.
Tear out center and fill with dip.
Use bread pieces to dip.

title: fiesta mexican pie
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Add 1/2 the chili powder and Cheez Whiz.
Cook until Cheez Whiz melts, stirring constantly.
Stir in tomato.
Combine remaining Cheez Whiz, eggs, flour, salt and milk in mixer bowl; beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Spoon ground beef mixture over batter to within 1-inch of edge.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hawaiian chicken wings
directions: Sprinkle defrosted drumettes with garlic salt or powder.
Put in large baking dish.
In separate saucepan, heat soy sauce, butter and sugar together until well blended.
Pour warm mixture over chicken and bake at 400° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting every 15 minutes or turning every 15 minutes, until nice and well done.

title: city chicken
directions: You will also need skewers (wooden, 5-inches in length).

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Let set 5 minutes.
Add pineapple and blueberries. Refrigerate until firm.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Spread on Jell-O mixture. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Ready to serve.

title: strawberry delight salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin in boiling water.
Put strawberries in hot gelatin and stir until melted.
Add crushed pineapple and syrup.
Stir well.
Pour into rectangular dish.
Chill for two hours or overnight.
Stir cream cheese and sugar together until fluffy.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla.
Spread over gelatin then sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Chill.
Cut into squares.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Beat in cooking oil, vanilla, baking soda and flour.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: spanakopita(spinach pie)
directions: Use this dish as a main dish or hors d'oeuvres.

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Coat pan with cracker crumbs.
Set aside.

title: open house punch
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Heat until dissolved. Cool and chill. Add other juices.
Chill until ready to serve.
Gently combine with cold ginger ale. Garnish. Serves 50.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and
teaspoon sugar in 1/2 cup warm water. Set aside until
yeast
rises
at least to top of cup, higher is okay.
Setting cup in cereal bowl of warm water will help it rise faster.
It rises in 15 minutes or so.

title: windy city cream cheese dip
directions: Toast pecans 2 to 3 minutes in oven at 350°.
Mix ingredients; add toasted pecans.
Refrigerate.
Serve as dip with crackers.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour butter into a 9-inch square pan; set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients, except peaches.
Pour this mixture into the buttered pan.
Arrange peach slices over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: ham spread or dip
directions: In blender or processor, combine cheese and margarine and process until smooth; add remaining ingredients and process until combined.
Serve on Melba toast or crackers, etc. or serve in a bowl with cut up vegetables.

title: white chicken chili
directions: In a large saucepan, combine 2 1/2 cups water with lemon pepper and cumin seed.
Boil.
Add chicken and cook on low 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Defat broth and return chicken to pan in the stock.

title: sweet sour red cabbage
directions: Simmer cabbage, cloves, salt, apples and water until tender (about 30 minutes).
Add vinegar, sugar, jam, butter and pepper. Then thicken with the cornstarch mixed with the 2 tablespoons water.
Stir until thick.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions, combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° cooking until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: pluma's country chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in 12x8 inch baking dish; cover with vegetables & seasonings. Combine soup & mayonnaise, gradually add water; mix until blended. Pour half of mixture over vegetables & rice; place chicken on top & add remaining mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: ranch corn flake chicken breasts
directions: Crush Corn Flakes in a sealed ziploc bag with a rolling pin. In a bowl, combine Corn Flakes, Cheese, and Dressing.
Dip Chicken in melted Butter, then roll in corn flake mixture to coat.
Pour left over Butter into a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350 for 50 minutes or until Chicken is completely cooked through.
Yields:
8 servings.

title: blueberry filling
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cook over low heat until thickened. Yield: 3 1/4 cups.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Cook brownies as directed on box and cool.
Beat margarine, sugar and creme de menthe until smooth.
Spread over cooled brownies.

title: redfish supreme
directions: Dress red fish, rub inside and out with salt, pepper and oil. Place on rack in roaster and add water.
(Do not let fish touch water.)
Cover and cook at 400° for about 40 minutes.
Save drippings.
To make sauce, melt butter in large saucepan.
Add flour, stirring constantly until golden brown.
Add finely chopped onion, celery, parsley and red pepper.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add drippings from roaster, water from mushrooms and enough plain water to make a thick, smooth sauce.
Saute mushrooms in butter in separate pan.
Place fish in a large flat baking dish, about 3 or 4 inches deep.
Cover with sauce.
Add sauteed mushrooms, oysters and shrimp.
Sprinkle grated cheese over and then sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° until well browned and bubbly, about 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: mary kay's artichoke dip
directions: Buckets of olives are sold in outdoor markets throughout France.
There really is no recipe for our favorite ... we love this.

title: crunchy chicken potato souffle
directions: Layer 2 cups potatoes, the chicken, mushrooms, water chestnuts, pimientos and onion in ungreased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch rectangular baking dish.
Mix eggs, milk, mayonnaise, pepper and soup; pour over chicken mixture.
Arrange cheese slices on top. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Heat oven to 300°.
Mix 1 cup potatoes and the margarine.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour or until potatoes are brown and chicken mixture is brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add mashed bananas and eggs.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Form into 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Chill at least 2 hours. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: pizza sauce i
directions: Cook tomatoes
until soupy, approximately 3 hours.
Add the rest of the ingredients,
except
tomato
paste and cook 1 hour. Add tomato paste and stir.
Put in jars and cook 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix good and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; then add eggs and flour (alternately), beating well between each addition (1 egg and part flour).
Add vanilla and beat well.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, sour cream and salad dressing.
Layer the remaining ingredients in order listed.
Pour dressing on top of layers.
Seal and refrigerate overnight.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Freeze in containers. Two hours before serving, take out of freezer.
Place in punch bowl.
Just before serving, add ginger ale. Serve slushy.
Makes enough for 50 punch cups.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Simmer chicken until done.
Debone.
Place chicken, soups, onion and chilies in a large pan. Bring to a slow boil.
Place chips in 9 x 10-inch pan.
Pour mixture over chips and sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix and marinate 12 hours.
Good for meat, chicken or fish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add cheese, cut in small pieces.
Add crackers, mashed fine.
Add milk and cream of mushroom soup.
Add a little celery.
Add small piece of onion cut fine.
Mix all together.
Pour in baking dish.
Add small pats of butter.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with crackers before cooking on top.
Then add butter.

title: the rabbi's vegetable kugel
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease a 10-inch casserole. Mix all ingredients together well. Pour into the baking dish. Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes. Raise oven to 350°; remove cover and bake an additional 15 minutes. Slice and eat hot as a vegetable; serve with a meat.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets.
Cool, peel and slice.
Fry bacon until crisp. Remove from skillet and drain on paper.
Saute onion in bacon fat until golden brown.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Carefully add potatoes and crumbled bacon.
Remove from heat.
Cover and place in a warm oven until ready to serve.
Best when made at least an hour before serving.

title: onion bites
directions: Soften margarine; stir in dry onion soup.
Spread on firm white bread.
Cut off crusts; cut into triangles or squares. Arrange on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fresh pueblo peach crisp
directions: Cut peaches into slices.
Mix sugar and salt and sprinkle over peaches in a shallow pan.
Combine flour and brown sugar in bowl; cut in butter until size of peas.
Sprinkle mixture over peaches. Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes or until topping is crumbly and brown.
Serve warm with cream or whipped topping.

title: poppy seed bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Liberally grease a 12-cup Bundt pan. Put cake mix, pudding mix and Dream Whip in mixer bowl; stir.
Add eggs and mix.
Add vegetable oil and water.
Beat for 4 minutes. Add poppy seed and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Pour into Bundt pan; bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Test at 50 minutes.
Let cake rest in pan 15 to 20 minutes before removing.
Top with Cinnamon Glaze (recipe follows).

title: dinner rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast into a large bowl.
Add warm water and stir until dissolved.
Add eggs, milk, butter, salt and sugar.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in 3 cups of flour, beating until smooth after each cup is added.
Add fourth cup; beat until dough is smooth and elastic.
Stir in 5th cup of flour to make stiff dough. Measure 6th cup of flour and sprinkle about half of it onto a breadboard or any flat surface.
Turn dough out onto the floured surface and with well-floured hands, knead dough until smooth and elastic (about 5 to 7 minutes).
Use remaining flour as needed.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown roast in oil.
Remove and set aside. In the drippings, saute onions and garlic until onions are tender. Return roast to Dutch oven.
Stir in tomatoes, 1/2 cup water, horseradish, browning sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove roast to a serving platter and keep warm.
Drain all but 2 cups of pan juices.
Combine flour and remaining water; stir into pan juices. Cook for 5 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Slice roast and serve with gravy.

title: pig in a blanket
directions: Boil cabbage about 15 to 20 minutes.
Then take leaves off. Mix hamburger meat and rest of ingredients good.
Take small amount of hamburger meat mixture to roll in cabbage leaves.
Place in a good sized pot.
Mix a can of tomato paste and 3 cans of water.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Cook on low heat until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Cook slow.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix gelatine with 4 tablespoons cold water.
Add boiling water.
Blend well.
Add crushed pineapple, sugar and lemon juice. Chill until slightly thickened.
Prepare 2 packages Dream Whip and fold into gelatine mixture.
Cut or tear your angel food cake into tiny to medium size pieces and stir your gelatine mixture into cake pieces until well mixed.
Pour into pan or glass dish and chill overnight.

title: coconut washboard cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll into balls; press with fork.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: dilled carrots
directions: Clean carrots and cut into thin strips.
Pack carrots into a jar with garlic, onion and fresh dill.
Bring vinegar and water to a boil.
Add salt and dill, if not using fresh dill.

title: salmon corn chowder
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Break into large chunks.
In saucepan, saute onion and celery in butter or margarine until tender.
Add condensed soup, milk and salmon liquid.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Add salmon and corn.
Heat thoroughly. Sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.	Add beaten eggs and salad oil, stirring by hand.
(Do not use mixer.)
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Spoon butter in 3 (9-inch) cake pans, greased and floured.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Let set in pans to cool for 10 minutes.
Remove and ice with cream cheese icing.

title: trifle
directions: Using an 8-inch diameter deep straight-sided glass dish, line bottom with broken Twinkies or sponge cake.
Reserving liquid, spoon fruit over the Twinkies.
Make Jell-O according to directions, making up to the two cups with the fruit cocktail juice and the sherry.
Pour over the Twinkies and fruit.
Allow to completely set.
Make Jell-O pudding according to directions, using slightly less milk.
Allow to completely set.
Top with cream.
Sprinkle with nuts (optional).

title: pound cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flavoring and butter in bowl.
Beat until creamy and smooth.
Combine remaining ingredients together in same bowl and beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or pound cake pan and bake for 90 minutes at 325°. Time may vary with different ovens.
Enjoy!

title: 6 minute broccoli souffle
directions: Heat the soup and cheese until it melts.
Stir in broccoli and egg yolks.
Cool slightly.
Fold in egg whites.
Put mix in 2-cup oven dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Add milk.
Mix well, using a wire whisk.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Mix well, using a whisk.
This takes a total of about 14 minutes, cooking on microwave High.
Stir after each 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter.
Can be cooked on top of stove.

title: oven stew
directions: Layer meat, potatoes, carrots, celery and onions in pot or casserole with lid.
Sprinkle tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper over top.
Pour juice over all.
Cover and cook in 250° oven for 4 hours, stirring once while cooking.
Add frozen peas; stir and finish cooking.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Let cool.
Punch holes in top of cake with fork.
Pour over top of cake Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut.
Top with Dream Whip made according to directions.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Blend margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla well.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Form into rolls on waxed paper. Chill.
(Will keep at least a week.)
Slice and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Stir peanuts into melted chocolate.
Spoon into candy paper cups.
Necessary chocolate can be purchased at a craft or candy shop.

title: spicy cajun shrimp
directions: Clean and devein shrimp
under cold water.
Drain well and set aside.
In a small bowl, combine the seasonings.
Combine margarine/butter, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings (cayenne pepper, black pepper, salt, red pepper, thyme, basil and oregano).
Mix in a large skillet over high heat. When the margarine/butter is melted, add the tomatoes, then the shrimp. Cook about 2 minutes, stirring evenly.
Add the beer and cover; cook for 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat.
Serve over rice accompanied with crusty French bread and a fresh garden salad. Serves 3 to 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix shortening, sugar and salt. Add boiling water and mix well.
Add eggs and stir.
Add flour and yeast mixture alternately to shortening.
Let rise until double in size.

title: party mints
directions: Cream butter.
Add water, salt and flavor.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Dust molds with granulated sugar.
Press in molds and unmold.

title: homemade lemonade
directions: Pour water in a gallon jug.
Add juice of lemons.
Pour in sugar.
Stir, then let it chill on ice.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 8-inch square pan, greased.
Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly (a pastry blender works very well) and spread over apples.
Bake in 375° oven until tender and brown, 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: In medium size bowl, mix ground beef, onion, salt and pepper well.
Shape into somewhat flattened loaf.
Wrap in double thickness of foil; cook on barbecue grill over indirect medium heat with the lid down for about 1 1/4 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a bowl; open foil and spread sauce over top.
Leave foil open; close lid.
Cook about 15 minutes more until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients, water and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing each well.
Pour into greased Bundt or angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Do not invert. When cool, tap sides and remove from pan.
Frost or glaze if desired.

title: iowa corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack in clean, hot jars; leave 1 inch headspace.
Make certain vinegar covers veggies.
Process 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: sauteed sirloin tips
directions: Saute sirloin tips.
Add mushrooms, onions, mushroom soup, sherry, garlic salt and water.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours. Serves 8.

title: crabmeat nippies
directions: Flake crabmeat and toss with mayonnaise and onion.
Spoon onto Melba toast.
Sprinkle generously with cheese.
Broil 3 inches from heat 1 to 2 minutes until cheese is melted and slightly browned.
Serve hot.
Makes 20 to 24 canapes.

title: original banana pudding
directions: Hint:
Dip bananas in lemon juice to keep from turning brown! Reserve 1 banana and 10 to 12 wafers for garnish.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator overnight for better flavor.

title: lazy day fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Heat fruit and sweeten to taste.
Pour in dish over butter, then add sugar, flour and milk mixture.
Pour over fruit.
Bake in oven at 350° until brown.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and let rise until doubled in size.
Form your loaves and place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise at least 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cover dough while rising.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans and sprinkle sugar on the bottom.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch frosting
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar slowly. Add milk and boil for 2 minutes. Chill thoroughly. Add confectioners sugar. Beat at high speed with electric mixer until thick enough to spread.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Beat cheese and butter.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, onion and pimento.
Mix well. Divide rolls into 4 squares and pinch perforations together. Fill squares.
Fold corners to middle and pinch.
Brush with butter. Sprinkle with crouton crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add eggs.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in raisins, nuts, applesauce and rolled oats. Pour batter into greased and floured ring mold, 1 1/2-quart size. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Loosen edges; cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.
Cool.
Frost with thin orange powdered sugar frosting.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Pour olive oil into large skillet.
When simmering hot, add shrimp; cook until golden brown.
Turn shrimp over, reduce heat. Add butter, garlic, salt and pepper.
When well blended, raise heat to hot, add vermouth and lemon juice, constantly stirring for one minute.
Serve over hot cooked rice or pasta.

title: sausage potato casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook sausage until no longer pink and drain.
In bowl, combine soup, milk, onions, salt and pepper.
In ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half of potato soup mixture and sausage.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mom's strawberry cake
directions: *Drain approximately 1/2 cup juice from the strawberries and save for cake.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix and chill for 2 hours.

title: fancy covered meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix ground beef with onion soup mix and form into 16 one-inch meatballs. Open rolls on a cutting board.
Cut the 8 rolls down the middle, making 16 pieces.
Press each one with palm of hand to flatten.
Place meatball on wide sides and roll up bringing sides together.
Put on cookie sheet and bake 13 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: coconut cheese pie
directions: Spread butter evenly over bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan. Press 1 1/3 cups coconut into butter, forming a shell.
Mix 1 cup coconut, the eggs, sugar, cheese and lemon juice.
Blend until smooth, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into coconut shell.
Sprinkle remaining coconut in a ring around top and in center.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: al-zahawiq(yemeni hot sauce)
directions: Liquidize and blend all ingredients.
Bring to the boil.
Cool and serve with bread as a dip or as a sauce with pasta, potatoes or meat.

title: summer salad
directions: Peel, seed and chop cucumbers.
Chop zucchini.
Mix salt and vinegar; toss with zucchini and cucumbers.
Let sit for 30 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and add.
Add vinegar, oil and salt and pepper to taste.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Put drinks and Eagle Brand in ice cream freezer and wait about 30 to 40 minutes for some good, easy ice cream.

title: spicy cranberries
directions: Combine 1/4 cup of water and sugar in small saucepan; add cinnamon .
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add berries and boil rapidly until berries pop, about 2 minutes. Chill.
Remove cinnamon and serve in hollowed out lemon cups. Makes 3/4 cup.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix the taco seasoning with the ground beef.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread refried beans on top of beef.
Add chilies.
Mix Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheeses. Place on top of chilies.
Pour on taco sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serve with nacho chips.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and Worcestershire. Then add crabmeat.
Put into baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and top with slivered almonds.
Bake until thoroughly heated.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers or Melba toast.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix.
Beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Alternate banana, vanilla wafers and pudding mix.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and salt.
Add flour and syrup. Bake in 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 35 minutes. Ice while hot.

title: lemonade
directions: Combine the sugar and lemon juice in a tall glass; add cold water.
Fill glass with ice.
Makes 1 glass.

title: classic spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine soup mix, sour cream and real mayonnaise.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts.
Cover; chill. Stir before serving.
Serve with Melba snacks.

title: chicken gumbo soup
directions: Place chicken, water, salt, pepper and celery tops in large kettle.
Cover and cook until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes. Remove chicken.
Add barley and cook 1 hour longer.
Remove chicken meat from bones and add with vegetables to broth;
cook an additional 30 minutes.

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage(toltott kaposta)
directions: Core one large head of cabbage; place in boiling water.
Take apart with knife and fork, cutting leaves as they become wilted. Drain and cool.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into 2 pie pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garden style cottage cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve on tomato flower and salad greens.
Serves 6.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all together and place in loaf pan.

title: country pork and sauerkraut
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook ribs and onion in oil until ribs are slightly browned and onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2-2 hours or until ribs are fork tender.
Serves 4.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Chop or spread cabbage, carrots, pepper and onions.
Mix vinegar, salt and sugar together. Mix all ingredients together and put in freezer bags or containers.

title: doughnuts
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and butter or margarine.
Cool to lukewarm. Measure warm water into large warm mixing bowl; sprinkle in yeast. Stir until dissolved. Add lukewarm milk mixture, egg and half the flour. Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough of remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth.

Knead until smooth and elastic about 5 to 10 minutes (grease hands with shortening or oil if dough sticks to them). Place dough in greased bowl, then turn greased side to top. Cover with damp cloth; let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: spinach, rice and bell pepper salad
directions: In medium bowl combine all ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Cover. Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: kistie's cheese ball
directions: *I use ones already chopped and sugared.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine garlic, sugar, salt, tomato juice, oil, lemon juice and Worcestershire in large bowl.
Beat until blended.
Stir in tomatoes, cucumber, green pepper, carrots, celery and green onion. Cover and chill for several hours.

title: hot dogs to take along
directions: Split hot dogs lengthwise.
Cook onions in butter until tender.
Mix onions, stuffing mix, water, catsup and relish together.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit; add bananas, pudding and poppy seed. Pour over fruit.

title: mutton loaf (navajo)(modern)
directions: Dice tomatoes and onions.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Form into a loaf and put into loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: In large skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat and cook cumin and chili powder 30 seconds.
Stir in meat sauce and beans.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes. Serve, if desired, over hot cooked rice and garnish with Monterey Jack cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Beat egg whites, baking powder and salt until thick.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until it holds peaks.
Fold in cracker crumbs, dates, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased pie pan and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cover with Cool Whip before serving.

title: pickled fish
directions: Mix fish, spices and onion together in a container with a lid.
Mix remaining ingredients and add.
Refrigerate for at least 7 days, stirring or shaking once or twice daily.

title: spiced pears, peaches, apples
directions: Cook sugar, vinegar, and spices 20 minutes. Drop in fruits, a few at a time, and cook until tender. Pack into hot, sterilized jars, adding syrup to within 1/2
inch of top. Seal. Makes 6 pints.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
In a large bowl, combine margarine, sugars, flour, cocoa and egg substitute until well blended.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread batter evenly in a well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into 2-inch squares while warm.

title: holiday shrimp dip
directions: In a bowl, beat cream cheese with a little clam juice, just enough to make it creamy, maybe a tsp or so.
Add Cream of Shrimp soup, continue beating.
Drain remainder of clams, add clams to soup mixture, add Parsley.
Add enough parsley to make it look pretty, it just gives it a little color.
Add Horseradish, now this is where personal taste comes into play, just don't overdue it too much can ruin it.
I, personally, like to have a little zing in mine, but not to much so my eyes water.
Chill before serving.
It can last a few days in the fridge, but when more green shows up then just the parsley, it is time to ditch it.

title: peanutty snowballs(cookies)
directions: Mix margarine, brown sugar, vanilla and flour until well blended.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Immediately press 1 whole peanut candy into top of each cookie.
Dust lightly with confectioners sugar.
Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: two bean soup
directions: Cover white beans with cold water and soak overnight.
Drain and place beans in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add ham and enough cold water to cover beans by 1 inch.
Bring water to a boil and simmer for about 1hour or until beans are tender.
Add green beans, celery, onion and potato.
Add enough water to cover the vegetables; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: potatoes with herbs
directions: In saucepan, boil unpeeled potatoes until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add basil, chives, lemon juice, oil and pepper to taste.
Mix lightly.
Serve.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain mixed vegetables.
Put in large pot.
Add hamburger and tomato juice.
Stir in brown gravy mix.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: mary's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs and salt until lemon colored. Add sugar and fold in syrup and melted butter a little at a time. Pour into pie shell.
Arrange pecan halves on top with broken side down.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: two minute chocolate fudge(microwave recipe)
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Microwave chocolate chips and the condensed milk uncovered in a 2-quart bowl on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in sugar and vanilla, then the walnuts until well blended.
Pour into greased pan and spread evenly.
Chill until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: cocktail fruit cake
directions: Mix.
Sprinkle over batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack in hot jars and pour solution over okra.
Heat in hot water bath 10 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: In top of double boiler, combine all ingredients, except vanilla.
Place over rapidly boiling water, beating on high speed until mixture stands in peaks, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Continue beating until frosting holds deep swirls (about 2 minutes).
Frosts a 13 x 9-inch cake or 2 layer cake.

title: seafood dip
directions: In a bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Serve over bread or crackers.

title: coney islands
directions: Mix ingredients.
Split hot dogs and fry in oil and onions. Brown and drain.
Pour mixture over hot dogs.
Simmer until thickened.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and eggs.
Add sour cream, soda, flour and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine the pumpkin, flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Cream well with electric mixer, then add the sugar, Crisco and eggs. Beat until well blended. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 round pans.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until done, stirring to crumble. Drain on paper towel and set aside.
Spread each slice of bread with butter; cut into cubes.
Place bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with sausage and top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour over mixture in baking dish.
Chill in refrigerator at least 8 hours.
Remove the dish from refrigerator and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
After cooking, cover and keep in refrigerator.
Slice and heat in microwave as needed.

title: almond float
directions: Put cold water in a square cake pan.
Sprinkle gelatine over the cold water.
Soften 5 minutes.
Sprinkle sugar.
Add hot water and stir until dissolved.
Add milk and almond extract. Refrigerate until set.

title: oysters for brunch at the hudson's
directions: Make a medium roux with butter and flour.
Stir in green onions and simmer until soft.
Blend in chicken broth, stirring continually.
Add shrimp and mushrooms and simmer about 10 minutes until mushrooms soften.
Beat egg yolk with wine.
Blend in a little of the hot mixture and stir all back into the sauce.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire, Accent, salt, pepper and Tabasco to taste.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese and paprika to color slightly.
Set aside.
Place oysters (on the shells) on a bed of rock salt in large pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Return oysters to shells, top with sauce and cover with crumb mixture.
Bake about 12 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serve with lemon wedges and thick slices of hot bread.

title: pudding cake
directions: Stir together the first 5 ingredients. Add the milk, 2 tablespoons cocoa and vanilla.
Mix all together with dry stuff. Add the nuts (optional).
Pour in an 8 x 8-inch ungreased pan. Spread.
Sprinkle the brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour the hot water over the batter.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
For a 9 x 13-inch pan, take all times 2.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Beat eggs at high speed until light and lemon colored. Gradually beat in sugar.
Reduce to low speed and beat in flour and butter; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and flavoring.
Turn into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with sweetened whipped cream or ice cream.

title: spicy cashew chicken
directions: Snap spaghetti in half, cook in boiling water until just tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water and set aside.
In 3-quart microwaveproof casserole, combine onion, carrots, oil and pepper flakes.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and celery.
Peel broccoli stem and slice thinly.
Cut off florets and separate them into bite size pieces.
Add broccoli and diced pepper to the casserole and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir in cashews and peas.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Cover and set aside.

title: easy chili beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and chili powder to taste.
Cook until well blended.

title: hocus pocus clam dip
directions: Drain clams, saving liquor.
Blend rest of ingredients except liquor into a paste.
Gradually add about 1/4 cup clam liquor and beat until consistency of whipped cream.
Chill. Serve with chips. Makes about 1 pint dip.

title: pasta with spinach and parmesan cheese
directions: Thaw spinach and press out excess liquid.
Heat oil with basil and garlic for a few minutes.
Add spinach and salt; cook and stir over low heat about 5 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese and milk to spinach.
Toss this mixture with fettucine until well blended. Serves 4 to 5.

title: delicious potatoes
directions: Place all the ingredients in greased casserole. Top with buttered corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham glaze
directions: Cook together for 10 minutes.
Cool and then glaze ham during last 30 minutes of baking.

title: pizza rolls(makes 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Unroll pizza crust on sprayed cutting board. Top with sauce, cheese and Parmesan. Sprinkle with garlic salt if you would like. Roll crust up and cut into 8 sections. They will look similar to cinnamon rolls. Arrange in a sprayed round baking pan. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars (brown and white) and eggs, beating until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Thoroughly stir together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Add oats and nuts.
Shape dough into two 8-inch rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: baked stew
directions: Brown stew meat in 1 teaspoon margarine.
Season with salt and pepper as you brown meat.
Remove meat and place in a baking dish with potatoes, carrots, green peas and onion which are cut up. Use drippings from browned meat and make gravy.
Put 1 teaspoon flour in a cup of cold water and pour into drippings (bouillon cubes may be added for additional flavor).
Simmer until thick. Pour over ingredients in baking dish until completely covered. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: kelly's lasagne
directions: Place hamburger and onion into a large pot.
Add sauce, paste, water, sugar, salt, pepper, spices and Parmesan cheese.
Cook on low for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cook noodles when sauce is done.
(The amount of noodles depends on how "meatier" you want.)

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Cream
the
butter
and
sugar	until light and fluffy. Stir together
flour and baking powder; set aside.
Beat eggs into oleo
mixture,
one
at a time, beating well after each. Add flour and milk alternately, mixing thoroughly. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan, or use 3 (8-inch) cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banders' favorite peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches and juice into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in order given:
mayonnaise, ketchup, sweet relish, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder. Refrigerate in glass jar or bottle.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, salt and oleo.
Add eggs, sour cream, vanilla, lemon and almond.
Sift in dry ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Dough is soft.
Use flour to roll out.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: red, white and blue pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat with 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla. Beat cream and 1/4 cup sugar until thick; fold into cheese mixture. Pour into cooled pie shells.
Make a well in the middle and pour 1/2 can blueberries into each.
Decorate outer edge with strawberries.

title: homemade sweet pickles
directions: Cut up the pickles.
Sprinkle sugar over top.
Drizzle vinegar over top.
Sprinkle pickling spice over top.
Do not stir.
Cover and let stand for 3 days.

title: monkey cake
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Roll biscuit quarters into balls, roll in sugar mixture and put into angel food or Bundt pan. Drizzle with a little of the butter mixture.
Continue until all the biscuits are used.
Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: nut crust
directions: Beat egg whites until a fine foam mounds gently around the beaters.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Beat well. Spread on pie and seal edge.
Brown at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rice in milk
directions: Clean the rice as for boiling in water.
Cook with the milk and salt, adding a few seeded and sultana raisins, if desired. Serve hot like boiled rice or press into small cups.
Cool and serve with cream and sugar.

title: twinkie pie
directions: Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan the Twinkies, cut in half longways.
Layer all other ingredients.
Top with cherries and chopped nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Prepare mix according to directions on the package; mix coffee.
Pour into wax lined glass loaf dish.
Microwave on 70% power for 5 minutes, rotate dish, then microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Let stand for 3 minutes.
Turn out on serving plate and sprinkle with mixture of sugar-cinnamon.

title: eggnog christmas salad
directions: Soften	gelatin
in
undrained pineapple and lime juice for 5 minutes.
Cook
and stir over medium heat until gelatin is dissolved.	Cool
to
room	temperature.
Stir
in	eggnog; chill until partially
set.
Fold in celery.
Turn into a 12 x 7 1/2
x 2-inch pan; chill until almost firm.
Heat cranberry juice until boiling.
Stir in raspberry jello until dissolved; chill until partially
set.
Fold in relish.
Carefully spoon on
top	of eggnog
mixture.
Chill
until
firm.
Cut	into squares.
Serve on	lettuce
leaf; garnish with roasted cranberries.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Add 1 quart cut up strawberries when crust is cooled.

title: cheese salad
directions: Mash a package of cream cheese until soft.
Add mayonnaise gradually; mix well.
Add cream, which has been whipped, then fold in chopped nuts, crushed pineapple and lemon juice.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
Serve on lettuce with salad dressing.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; cut in the butter.
Add milk and mix.
Pour in a greased baking pan.
Cover with 2 cups fruit.
Sprinkle 1 cup (or less) sugar over fruit and dot with butter.
Add one cup fruit juice.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Batter will come to top.
Serve topped with cream.

title: macaroni salad 1
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions. Drain. Add other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°; melt two tablespoons margarine over low heat; add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper.
Slowly stir in milk, stirring until thick and smooth.
Add 3/4 of the cheese and then stir into milk mixture until cheese is melted.
Transfer cooked macaroni to lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour cheese over macaroni and toss to coat.
Top with reserved cheese.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and sour cream.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat at medium speed for 6 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at lowest speed just until blending after each addition.
Stir in flavors.
Pour in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix well in order given.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Press down a little.
Bake until light brown in 350° oven.

title: refreshing "new potato" salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together salad dressing, dill and pepper. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate cake(made with chocolate syrup)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with syrup. Add vanilla.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured pans (about 8-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach in strainer; squeeze out excess water.
Mix together all ingredients, except noodles.
Break noodles into 1/2-inch pieces and add to dip.
Add noodles less than 1 hour before serving so they don't get soggy.

title: chili puffed eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in chilies.
Pour into pan.
Bake until lightly browned and tester comes out clean, about 45 minutes.
Serve with salsa and chopped cilantro on the side. Serves 8.

title: pickle fans
directions: Cut pickle into thin parallel slices, almost the full length of the pickle.
Spread carefully into a fan shape.

title: crab cakes ala sally
directions: Sort crabmeat to remove shells.
Crumble the bread into fine crumbs.
To the crab meat, add the crumbs and the rest of the ingredients.
Mix and shape into patties.
Saute in a mixture of vegetable oil and butter until lightly brown on each side.
Makes about 6 good sized cakes.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix with cocoa.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, cake coloring, eggs and margarine.
Blend until moistened.
Add soda to vinegar and mix into cake mixture.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 350° in layer pans for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan.
This makes 3 layers.

title: cinnamon "surprise" toast
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Place 3 slices of bread on pan under a broiler; toast one side.
Remove from broiler; spread untoasted side with mixture.
Return to broiler; let cook until mixture bubbles (1 minute).

title: chocolate marshmallow fudge
directions: In a heavy pan, melt the margarine. Add the evaporated milk and sugar and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil rapidly for 5 minutes; keep stirring. Remove from heat and immediately add the chocolate chips and marshmallow cream. Beat until all is blended. Add walnuts. Pour into a greased baking pan and let it cool.

title: triple layer cookie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Put graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Top with coconut and milk.
Then bake 25 minutes or until lightly brown. Melt over low heat the chips and peanut butter.
Pour this over other.
Let set.
Then cut into squares.

title: potato casserole
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Use shortening to fry potatoes.
Leave skin on potatoes; cut round.
Cut onion round.
Cook onion and potatoes together.
When done, add beaten eggs and cubed or shredded cheese and bacon.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Flour fruit and combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° about 35 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar, pour over this mixture boiling water and let cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water, add to the Crisco mixture.
Then add well-beaten eggs.
Add salt and flour and stir well.
Put in bowl, grease top and cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out and let stand 3 hours before baking.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: apple breakfast sausage
directions: Mix the ingredients in a large bowl and shape into 1/2-inch thick patties.
Spray rack of broiler pan with nonstick spray coating.
Arrange patties on unheated rack.

Broil 4 to 5 inches from the heat about 10 minutes or until no pink remains; turn once. (Or spray a large skillet with nonstick spray coating and cook sausage over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until no pink remains.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put in unbaked pie shell, then add top. Put vent holes in top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken yakitori
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken.
Mix thoroughly; pour over chicken cubes.
Marinate, covered.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender. Drain and place in a greased casserole dish.
Make a sauce of the butter, flour, salt, milk, pepper and cheese.
Pour sauce over the broccoli. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and cooked bacon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbling hot and browned on top.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on round pizza pan.
Gently spoon on chili and vegetables.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until shredded cheese is melted.
Serve with nachos.

title: aunt nora's egg pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and flour, mixed, then milk and butter. Bake in an uncooked crust till it sets.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Whip together (blend) or beat together.
Should liquify. Serve with fruit.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.

title: western hash
directions: Brown ground beef; add tomatoes, green peppers, onion, rice, basil and pepper. Cover and simmer 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. When rice is cooked, top with cheese slices. Heat until cheese is melted. Serves 6.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites with salt and cream of tartar until foamy. Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition, then continue beating to very stiff peaks.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch pie plate to form nestlike shell.
Build sides up 1/2-inch above edge of pan. Bake in slow oven (300°) for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Stir chocolate in the water over low heat until melted.
Cool until thickened.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Whip cream; fold into chocolate mixture.
Pile into shell.
Chill 2 hours.

title: veal and peas
directions: Preheat pan; add olive oil (2 ounces).
Saute veal 1 minute on each side, turn, cook for one minute and remove to side plate. Add red sauce; bring to a simmer.
Add veal.
Season to taste. Add peas.
Heat vegetables.
Serves 2.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown chops; remove and drain off fat.
In buttered 2-quart casserole, arrange potatoes, mushrooms and chops.
