In small bowl, mix water and onion soup mix.
Stir.
Pour over meat.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: stuffed zucchini with fresh tomato
directions: Wash zucchini; cut off stems.
Cut each in half crosswise. In a small amount of boiling water with 1/2 teaspoon salt in a large saucepan, cook zucchini, covered, for 5 minutes, or until just tender.
Drain well; cool and scoop out seeds.
In skillet, melt butter.
Saute garlic until golden; lift out and discard. Add onion; saute, stirring, until golden.
Add tomato, rice, oregano, salt and cayenne.
Toss with fork to mix well.

title: make ahead pie crust
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Blend in shortening until crumbly.
Combine water, vinegar and egg.
Beat lightly with fork. Pour into dry mixture.
Blend until sticky.
Chill 2 hours. Divide into 4 or 5 balls or roll out to fit pie pans.
Wrap securely and refrigerate or freeze.

title: easiest picnic salad
directions: Take bananas unpeeled, pineapple and peanuts unopened and enough salad dressing in a jar.

Just before serving time, assemble peeled and sliced bananas, drained pineapple and salad dressing in servings bowl (which of course you have remembered to bring, along with a knife to slice bananas and a can opener to open the pineapple).
Just before serving, add peanuts and stir. Caution; don't add the peanuts too soon.
They get soggy.
This salad requires no refrigeration in transit to the picnic site and minimal preparation at serving time.
This is a favorite at our house, where we often make individual bowls.
It also can serve as a dessert after a heavy main course.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix well, then add your fruit (mandarin oranges, pineapple either crushed or chunk).
Mix gently.
Refrigerate.

title: sauerkraut and noodle casserole
directions: Put noodles to cook in plenty of boiling salted water.
Drain sauerkraut; rinse in cold water and drain again.
Spread about 3/4 of sauerkraut in a greased shallow 1 1/2-quart dish.
When noodles are barely tender, drain and add butter.
Toss and spread over sauerkraut.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and most of cheese.
For color, add a few strips of pimento.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature; blend.
Form into 2 balls and roll in chopped nuts.

title: english muffin pizza(children)
directions: Place English muffins on a cookie sheet.
Place on top rack of oven.
Turn oven onto broil. Set oven temperature to 400°. Remove from oven when slightly brown.

title: frito salad
directions: Note:
Mix right before time to serve.

title: cavetelli
directions: Heat water, milk and margarine.
Cool.
Add beaten eggs, salt, baking powder and potatoes.
Add flour, knead well.
Keep dough covered.
Roll 1/8 of dough out on lightly floured surface to pencil thickness.
Cut into 1 inch pieces.
Allow to dry on lightly floured board about 4 hours.
Dough may be frozen for future use or cooked in boiling water until they rise to the surface.

title: pizza chicken
directions: In a large bowl, put flour and coat your chicken on all sides; set aside.
In a large frying skillet, put your oil or shortening and put on a medium flame to heat until a little drop of flour dropped into it sizzles.
This keeps your chicken from getting greasy.
When grease is ready, fry chicken to a golden brown. Take chicken out when done and drain on a paper towel.
In the bottom of a long baking dish, put a layer of pizza sauce.
Place chicken on top of pizza sauce and sprinkle with oregano.
Put the rest of the pizza sauce over the chicken; top with Mozzarella cheese and put in a 350° oven until cheese is a medium golden brown.
Serves 4.
Your kids will want this as often as you will fix it.

title: machine shed's baked potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in water for 10 minutes; drain and set aside. In a large heavy pot, saute the bacon, onion and celery over medium-high heat until celery is tender and bacon is crisp. Drain the bacon grease from the onion, celery and bacon. Add milk, the 1 quart of water, chicken base, salt and pepper. Heat until hot, but not boiling. In a heavy large saucepan, melt the margarine and add the flour (to make a roux). Mix well and allow to bubble for 1 minute. While constantly stirring, add the flour and margarine mixture to the milk mixture, very slowly. Continue stirring until thick and creamy. Stir in potatoes, parsley and whipping cream. Serve while hot. Garnish with shredded Colby cheese, fried bacon bits, chopped green onion or all 3.

title: grandma beadnell's pink salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Drop in marshmallows, cut in fourths.
Stir until melted.
Let stand until set.
Beat in 1/2 pint whipping cream and the crushed pineapple with mixer.
Stir in nuts.
Let set until firm.
Keep refrigerated.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix the eggs with buttermilk.
Add melted butter.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk to hotcake consistency.
Bake in a 2-inch buffet or steam table pan at 400° until done.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Mix together and marinate for 48 hours in refrigerator.
Makes enough for 25 chops.
Delicious cooked on the grill.

title: cranberry baked beans
directions: Wash beans and add to 1 1/2 quarts water in a large saucepan. Boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain off liquid, reserving 1 cup. Pour beans, 1 cup bean water and remaining ingredients into a crock-pot.
Cook on low for approximately 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: three bean salad
directions: Heat until sugar melts.
Marinate 24 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, green pepper, cabbage and rice. Stir in tomatoes and paste, water, salt, pepper and bay leaf. Heat mixture to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Alternate adding milk and dry ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: helen's portuguese stew
directions: Slice sausage 1/4-inch thick slices. Brown in 12 or 14-inch skillet on medium heat. Brown both sides of slices approximately 10 to 12 minutes. Mince garlic and stir thoroughly into skillet as sausage browns. Slice pepper into 1/4 x 2-inch slices. Dice onion. When sausage is browned, add pepper and onion. Continue medium heat and stirring, cook 5 minutes. Add kidney beans, tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and chili powder. Stir thoroughly and continuously approximately 5 minutes. Add and stir in water; reduce heat and let cook down, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Result should be a nice thick dark brown sauce with sausage, peppers, onions and tomatoes visible. This is a fun one pan easy quick meal that can be adjusted to taste and will fill the kitchen with a wonderful fragrance. Serve with buttered hard rolls and a green salad or for a real treat with buttered sun-dried tomato bread.

title: mexican corn bread casserole
directions: Combine cornmeal, baking soda and salt.
Stir in milk, eggs and corn.
Stir in cheese, chili peppers and onion; mix well.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in kidney beans, tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic powder; cook until heated through.
Grease and sprinkle a thin layer of cornmeal over the bottom of a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Empty half cornmeal batter into dish.
Cover with meat/bean mixture and top with remaining cornmeal batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut fingers
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut; mix well.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonful into coconut; roll like fingers.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with whisk 30 seconds. Add lemonade concentrate. Beat with wire whisk 30 seconds (mixture will be thick). Immediately stir in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish with lemon slices, if desired. Store leftover pie in the refrigerator. Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon pecan cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 cup flour to chopped fruit, raisins and nuts.
In 2nd bowl, combine remaining flour (2 3/4) with baking powder and salt.
In a 3rd bowl, beat egg whites until stiff (but moist); set aside.

In a 4th very large mixing bowl with your electric mixer on high speed, cream butter, margarine and sugar.	Add extract and egg yolks (slightly beaten). Gradually beat in flour mixture; next add the floured fruit mixture.
After all is well mixed, fold in egg whites.
Pour into tube pan (sprayed with Pam and well floured).
Bake for 1 hour at 300°; reduce oven to 250° and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Once baked, leave in pan until cool.
Then remove from pan; cover with a large bowl overnight.
Next day, wrap well with Saran Wrap and foil.
Keep in refrigerator and it will keep for weeks.
The bowl is very heavy and having someone to help you is great.

title: chili sauce dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with crisp raw vegetables and/or tortilla chips.
Yield: About 1 1/2 cups.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbages.
Cook in 2 cups water for 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside. Mix margarine, flour, salt, pepper, milk and green peppers.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add Cheez Whiz.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need a plastic flowerpot.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: In large bowl, combine first eight ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture and coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator. Remove chicken from marinade.
Coat each piece with bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Add milk. Combine flour, salt and soda and add to mixture. Add mashed bananas and mix well. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake in oven at 350° about one hour.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients.
Pour over chicken in shallow baking dish.
Cover with clear wrap and marinate at least 1 hour in refrigerator, but no more than 3 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes if boned or 1 hour if whole.
Serve leftover liquid over cooked rice.

title: paprika potatoes
directions: Dice onion and green pepper, lightly brown in oil.
Plank cut potatoes.
Add to pot with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover with water and cook till tender.
Add sausage when potatoes are half way done.
Water should blend in with potatoes.

title: one skillet spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onions in a 10-inch skillet until hamburger is light brown, drain.
Stir in tomatoes (with liquid), green pepper, water, mushrooms, salt, sugar, chili powder and spaghetti.
Break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer, stirring ocasionally, until spaghetti is tender, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: chili sauce
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes; cut them in small pieces and put with all other ingredients into a granite saucepan.
Cook very slowly for three hours and then can and seal.

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in 1/2 cup water.
In a large bowl combine dissolved yeast, rest of water, shortening, sugar and salt.
Add flour a little at a time. When all flour has been added, knead well.
Let rise. Turn onto floured board and knead again. Divide in half. Form two long loaves.
You can use a French bread pan or cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Combine water and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add pie filling and return to a boil.
Pour boiling mixture over gelatin, stirring to dissolve.
Add pineapple and juice, lemon juice, cola and nuts. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: cracker salad
directions: Finely chop celery, green onions, tomatoes and bell pepper. Combine in bowl. Add mayonnaise and crackers after crumbling. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Boil chicken; salt slightly.
Cut up celery and cover with stock.
Simmer 15 minutes (keep pot covered at all times).
Then add cut up onion and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
Keep adding stock as needed.
Then add about 1 teaspoon of molasses and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce.
Add cut up chicken and bean sprouts. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Let it all simmer about 10 minutes.
Then add flour or cornstarch paste to thicken.
(I add all my chicken stock to make a good pot full.
Try adding a can of chow mein vegetables if you like.)
Thicken only what you intend to use.
Freeze the remaining chow mein.
Thickened chow mein doesn't freeze well.

title: cheese corn bread
directions: Heat the oil in a small skillet.
Add the minced onion and saute over medium heat until the onion is soft and translucent. Set aside to cool.
Beat together egg, sugar and milk.
Combine flour, corn meal, baking powder and salt.
Mix thoroughly. Combine flour mixture with egg mixture.
Mix until well blended. Add corn, sauteed onions and grated cheese.
Mix well.
Spread into a buttered 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned and firm on top.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine; add coconut and chopped pecans.
Brown lightly in oven; set aside.
Combine softened cream cheese and milk, using mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put 1/4 of this mixture into each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 jar of caramel sauce on each.
Sprinkle with 1/4 of the coconut and pecan mixture on each pie and repeat layers. Freeze.
Serve right from freezer.

title: diet cheese pie
directions: Put 1/4 cup pineapple juice and gelatine in a cup and stir. Put into the microwave and bring to a boil.
Put this gelatine into the bowl of creamed cottage cheese.
Add all other ingredients and mix well with a spoon.
Spray a pie pan with Pam spray.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and refrigerate.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot and simmer for 10 minutes. Mixture will keep refrigerated for several weeks.
Can be reheated when ready to use.
Great for those who don't like apple cider.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all; cook to 300°.
Pour on wax paper.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan.
Set aside.
Into a 2-quart heavy saucepan, place sugar, salt, butter and evaporated milk.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium-high heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Boil 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add chocolate and marshmallow creme; stir vigorously and speedily until chocolate is melted and mixture is uniform in color.
At once, stir in the nuts and pour into desired size squares.
Store in airtight container.

title: scrull
directions: Add sugar to melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix all together.
Put 1 teaspoon on Scrull iron.
Take off and roll in cone shape.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup in deep pan.
Bring to a boil. Cook to hard ball stage.
Slowly pour over egg whites while beating with electric beater.
Beat until candy clings to spoon and loses most of its shine.
Spread on smooth surface; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Spread generously with peanut butter.
Roll into one large roll; divide into 2 rolls.
Cut into desired pieces.

title: ham and cheese chowder
directions: Combine the vegetables and seasonings in a large saucepan; heat to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until the vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.

title: the temperance inn's shrimp cayenne
directions: Combine all spices.
Add shrimp and toss.
Heat 12-inch cast-iron skillet until very hot and almost smoking.
Add butter. Brown shrimp, turning once.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add wine and cook until reduced by half.
Remove skillet from heat.
Add the cold butter and stir well.
Serve at once.

title: crawfish and rice casserole
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients. Pour into casserole dish.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot and spicy chicken wings
directions: Deep fry wings or drumsticks 5 to 10 minutes.
Place meat in baking dish after frying.
Melt butter and sauce together.
Place dish under broiler and cover meat with sauce.
Cook until golden brown.
This is very good out on the grill.

title: chicken scallop
directions: Prepare according to directions or as you normally do.

title: parmesan-caraway appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients until stiff dough forms.
Drop by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls about 1 inch apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, about 8 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen appetizers.

title: individual zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Form into individual pancakes.
Cook in small amount of cooking oil in skillet, browning pancakes on both sides.
Yield:
Serves 4.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple chunks and juice in bottom of casserole dish. Mix flour and sugar.
Pour over pineapple.
Melt butter and crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle crackers over mixture and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot spinach and bacon
directions: Place bacon in 3-quart microproof casserole.
Cover with paper towels.
Cook on High 2 minutes, or until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain, cool and crumble.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon drippings from casserole.
Add onion.
Cover.
Cook on High 1 1/2 minutes, or until onion is transparent.
Stir in vinegar and sugar.
Add spinach; mix lightly.
Cover.
Cook on High 6 to 7 minutes, or until spinach is tender, stirring once during cooking time; stir. Drain.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Serve hot.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Spoon broccoli in buttered baking dish.
Arrange chicken over broccoli.
Pour mixture of soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice over layers.
Sprinkle with mixture of cheese, melted butter, and bread crumbs. Dot with 2 Tbsp butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: never fail meringue for 9-inch pie
directions: Beat on high speed, egg whites with a pinch of salt until whites hold soft peaks.
Add Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until you can draw a finger through mixture and it holds the groove about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: little sweet potato pies(empanadas de camote)
directions: Cook the sweet potatoes until they are almost dry.
Mash, then add margarine, sugar and spices.
Make sure the mixture is dry. Prepare pastry dough and make dough into little balls about the size of a silver dollar.
Then with rolling pin, roll each ball as thin as you can.
Put about a teaspoon of filling in the middle and fold the crust over and seal with the edge of a fork.
Lay pies on a cookie sheet and bake in a hot oven at 425° until they almost get toasted, then take out and with a little brush spread 1/2 teaspoon Eagle Brand milk on each pie.
Return to oven about 5 more minutes or until brown on top.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Gently mix in chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° about 14 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Add half and half and cheese.
Simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and boil first 5 ingredients 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Spread on greased pan or plate.

title: iowa pork chop marinade
directions: Marinate chops 4 to 6 hours in refrigerator.
Brown over hot coals 2 to 4 minutes each side.
Stand chops up on backbone and grill covered for 14 minutes.

title: hurry up cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Chill.

title: tuna souffle
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk; cook over low heat until sauce boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Thoroughly beat egg yolks.
Add white sauce, gradually stirring to keep smooth.
Add onion, salt, pepper, parsley and flaked tuna.
Cool slightly.
Carefully fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into ungreased 6-cup casserole. Bake at 325° about 1 hour or until puffy and high and delicately browned on top.
Serve immediately.
Makes 5 generous servings.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Sprinkle salt over tomatoes and let set 1 hour; drain.
Cover with boiling water and let set 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients and cook until mixture is boiling hot.
Put into jars and leave 1-inch headspace.
Put on lids and rings. Process 25 minutes at 10 pounds pressure or 2 hours in hot water bath.

title: whiskey balls
directions: Mix first five ingredients. Mix whiskey and corn syrup and mix well. Pour over dry ingredients. Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar. Store in tight container.

title: best lemon meringue pie
directions: Prepare and bake pastry shell; cool.
In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Gradually add hot water, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over high heat until mixture comes to a boil; reduce heat, cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks, then return egg mix to saucepan; bring to boil, cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and lemon peel; slowly add juice and mix well.
Pour into shell; spread meringue over filling.
Seal edges. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: quick punch
directions: Mix 7-Up and pineapple juice. Chill. Just before serving, add sherbet, any flavor.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello and fruit juices.
Chill until slightly jelled.
Add fruit.
Chill until set.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except eggs.
Put half of mixture in buttered casserole (9 x 13-inch).
Lay egg slices flat on top of mixture.
Put rest of mixture on top. Sprinkle with stuffing mix to cover top, then add almonds.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Nuts may be used, if desired.
Also crushed pineapple may be used instead of pineapple chunks.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put potatoes, sausage and cheese in layers in pot.
Add salt and pepper.
Add soup and milk.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour, stirring once.
Do not fill pot to top as it will boil over.

title: angel food cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add egg, then dry ingredients.
Stir in coconut and vanilla.
Roll into small balls, then roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool. Yields about 4 dozen.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine flour and salt in bowl; cut in shortening until it resembles coarse meal.
Add water and stir until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Shape into a ball and chill.
Roll pastry to fit casserole dish.

title: frozen pineapple-lemon pie
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 1 tablespoon juice.
In a large mixing bowl, combine pineapple, topping, nuts, lemon peel, lemon juice and reserved pineapple juice.
Stir together until well blended.
Spoon into prepared crust.
Cover well and freeze until firm or overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: frosty mandarin dessert
directions: Drain orange sections, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sherbet by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until thickened.
Fold oranges, reserving a few for garnish.
Pour into a serving bowl or individual serving dishes.
Chill until set, at least 1 hour. Garnish with reserved mandarin oranges and mint leaves, if desired.
Makes about 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: relish
directions: Combine with listed ingredients.
Put in jars and seal.

title: apple yorkshire pudding
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon evenly over pan.
Arrange apples over this mixture.
Sift together flour and salt.
Beat eggs until light; add flour and 1/2 cup milk.
Beat until well blended.
Gradually add last cup milk and beat until smooth.
Pour batter over the apples.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut the 2 loaves into 32 pieces (each loaf).
Dip each, first into butter, then into dry ingredients mixture.
Continue until all are used.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool 10 minutes, then invert pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook onion, mushrooms, green pepper and pimento pepper in butter for 5 minutes.
Blend flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream; heat but do not boil.
Stir in beans and cheese. Pour into greased casserole dish and top with corn flakes; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix next 4 together to make a dressing.
Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Best after 12 hours.
This will last until all eaten up.

title: breakfast potato pie
directions: Cover hash browns with hot water; let stand 10 minutes.
Drain well.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar and cook about 5 minutes or until soft.
Add 1 package wild strawberry Jell-O.
Pour into jars and refrigerate.

title: hasenpfeffer(german)
directions: Heat in a Dutch oven 3 tablespoons fat.
Add rabbit pieces and brown slowly, turning to brown evenly.
Remove from heat. Gradually add 2 cups of the marinade.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: crunch pea salad
directions: Mix all together and garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in lightly greased crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high setting until cheese begins to melt (30 minutes), stirring well, occasionally.
Cover and continue to cook on high setting until mixture is smooth and cheese is melted.
Add more milk, if needed, for dipping consistency.
Turn to low setting for 3 to 4 hours.
Just before serving, remove cover.
Serve as a hot dip with Melba toast rounds.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in mayonnaise-oiled baking dish and top with crumbled Cheez-Its crackers and sprinkle paprika on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: orange sherbet gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add sherbet and mix well.
When partially set, add other. Pour into 1 1/2-quart ring mold. Chill. Yields 8 servings.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Mix half of the soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs and seasoning.
Press firmly into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add potatoes and top with remaining soup and cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.
Garnish with fried bacon, if desired.

title: cheese hash brown potatoes
directions: Melt cheeses and margarine together and add milk.
Pour over potatoes and bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: beer bread
directions: Stir with wooden spoon until well mixed.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Pour margarine or butter over batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature. Cream and gradually stir in drained pineapple until smooth. Add 1 cup pecans and chives. Chill mixture well. Place on plate and form into ball. Sprinkle pecans on top. Chill until serving time.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix and reserve.
Spread pecans and coconut in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cake mix over nuts.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients until crumbly.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix all remaining ingredients in mixer until well blended.
Pour over warm crust. Bake at 350° for an additional 25 minutes; cool.
Cut into small squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: middle eastern spicy carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salt water with garlic (about 10 minutes). Combine all other ingredients.
Drain carrots and toss with spices.
Cover.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Split peppers lengthwise; remove seed and stems. Wash and drop into a large pot of boiling salted water. Turn off heat and let stand for 5 minutes; drain. Arrange in baking dish. Saute onion and celery in butter for 5 minutes. Mix onion, celery, beef, rice, salt and 1 can of tomato sauce. Fill peppers with meat mixture. Combine 1 can tomato sauce with water and wine; pour over peppers. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 20 minutes longer. Serves 8.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Work with hands.
Force dough through cookie press onto ungreased baking sheet in desired shapes.
Bake until set, not brown, at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes. Yields 6 dozen.

title: holly's calico bars
directions: Mix butter and cracker crumbs.
Press in 9 x 12-inch pan. Layer, starting with coconut, chocolate chips and condensed milk, ending with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside. Melt shortening and stir in brown sugar. Allow to cool slightly. Beat in eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each. Add flour mixture, nuts and chocolate chips. Blend well. Pour into greased pan, 9 x 12. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. When almost cool, cut into squares.

title: creamy walnut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and white sugar in large bowl.
Add brown sugar, shortening and 3/4 cup milk.
Mix until flour is dampened.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs, 1/4 cup milk, maple flavoring and walnuts.
Beat 1 minute.

title: noodles
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Knead until firm and smooth.
Roll out thin; let dry until they can be cut without sticking.
Let dry thoroughly.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix the hash browns, 1 stick melted butter, soup and cheese. Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Mix 1/2 stick melted butter and the corn flakes.
Spoon on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add salt and beaten eggs.
Mix well. Add rhubarb and berries.
Mix well again and pour into pie crust. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: crab imperial
directions: Melt margarine in pan. Mix in flour.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly to keep smooth.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Mix in onion, Worcestershire sauce and bread cubes.
Cool.
Fold in
mayonnaise, salt and pepper.

title: mexically option
directions: I love this recipe because I can change it up and use whatever optional ingredients I want to.
For example, I don't use flour tortillas and Doritos.
I use either one or the other.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: corn-stuffed pork chops
directions: Mix corn with liquid, bread cubes, onions, salt and sage. Stuff pork chop pockets with corn mixture.
Melt shortening in large skillet; brown chops about 15 minutes.
Reduce heat; cover tightly and simmer 1 hour or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crullers
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended. Roll into a thin dough. Cut into squares or triangles.
Make
a slit in the center and
pull one end through this slit.
Deep fry these in hot shortening until delicately browned.
Remove from fryer and drain well on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cooled.

title: quick pigs in a blanket
directions: Boil wieners until done.
Roll biscuits out flat; split hot dogs in middle and fill with cheese and onions and roll up wieners in dough.
Bake until brown at 425°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups and milk.
Add beans to soup mixture along with salt, chicken, onion, celery, noodles and almonds.
Turn mixture into a 2 quart greased casserole or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Top with French fried onions (crush them in your hands) and bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and boil 2 minutes.
Stir constantly to avoid sticking.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; spoon onto wax paper or fill cupcake papers.

title: cucumbers and onions
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers in salt water as long as desired. Drain and cover with sliced onions. In a separate bowl combine other ingredients. Pour over cucumbers. Refrigerate.

title: picnic style chicken breast
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Place chipped beef in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Wrap each chicken breast with bacon strip (after rolling up breast).
Can secure with toothpick if needed.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry onion in butter until delicately brown.
Strain butter into saucepan.
Add potatoes, milk, corn, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Bring to the boiling point and serve.
Good with oyster crackers.

title: apple cream cake
directions: Mix walnuts, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar together in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Cream butter and remaining sugar together.
Set aside.
Beat eggs and vanilla together until light and fluffy. Sift in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture along with sour cream.

title: silken tofu
directions: Put peanuts into 6 cups water in a pan.
When water boils, turn to simmer for 2 hours.
Add 4 cups water, milk, sugar and tofu.
Bring to boiling point.
Tofu may be served hot or cold.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat together sugar, vegetable oil and eggs. Stir in bananas and lemon rind. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture and stir until combined. Fold in nuts.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: old-fashion greens
directions: Select tender greens and remove stems.
Add ham hock or country ham to water and boil for 20 to 30 minutes; add chili pepper or Tabasco.
While water is boiling, wash greens good, swishing them good to get all sand off; lift from water and drain. Rinse at least 3 times.
Add greens to boiling water; reduce to simmer and cook slowly until greens are tender.
Serve with pepper vinegar.

title: microwave rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Microwave for 6 minutes, stirring twice.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion and tomato sauce.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed.
Beat egg and add cheese and parsley flakes, if desired. Layer meat mixture, noodles and cheese mixture.
Sprinkle 1 cup Mozzarella cheese between layers.
End with meat mixture. Sprinkle other cup Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese on top. Cover; cook 20 minutes at 375°.
Uncover; cook 20 minutes at 375°.

title: mother's gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 9-inch pans or a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
With electric mixer, cream the sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add molasses.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Wash and dry eggplant; trim ends.
Do not pare; slice into 1/4-inch thick rounds.
Sprinkle with salt; layer slices in a colander. Cover and let drain for 1 hour; dry slices with paper towels.
Beat eggs and flour until smooth.
In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Dip eggplant in egg-flour mixture and slowly brown on both sides in hot oil; add more oil as needed. Add a layer of eggplant to a shallow 2-quart baking dish (approximately 12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Heat tomato sauce and cover eggplant; sprinkle with oregano and some of the cheese.
Continue to layer in this way.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until hot, 25 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: turkey croquettes
directions: Mix well the turkey, onion and Mrs. Dash.
Shape into 3 ounce patties.
Roll in cereal and place on baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes or until fork will remove clean.

title: three bean bake
directions: Brown ground beef and bacon.
Add onion.
Cook until bacon is crisp.
Drain kidney and butter beans.
Add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: real key lime pie
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk, egg yolks and Key lime juice together until well blended.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill. Spread Cool Whip and chill until ready to serve.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well, then add
milk,
if needed.
Drop by spoonful into hot oil.
Cook until brown.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter or margarine in saucepan; bring to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper or cookie sheet.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Puree cucumbers, scallions and fresh mint or dill with chicken stock.
Add sour cream and chill.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat salad dressing, cake mix, eggs, water and cinnamon until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool completely.
Spread cake with frosting.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients in 1/2 cup boiling water; add 1/2 cup to this.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: sausage roll or pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add oil and stir.
Add salt and 3 cups flour.
Mix into stiff dough.
Turn out on flat surface with remaining flour.
Knead until smooth and elastic, using more flour, if needed.
Place in oiled bowl, cover and let rise until double in bulk, about 2 hours.

title: hidden orange mounds
directions: Set measured cookie mix aside while cutting each piece of candy into quarters.
Wrap about 1 teaspoon of dough around each piece of candy.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crabmeat cheese wedges
directions: Let cheese and butter stand at room temperature until soft. Mix cheese, butter, crabmeat and seasonings until well blended. Spread mixture on 12 English muffin halves.
Cut each half into 8 wedges.
Broil until golden.
Makes 96 wedges.

title: chicken salad riviera
directions: Combine pineapple, chicken, peas, celery, grapes, almonds, and onion in a bowl.
Toss with Sunny Dressing.
Serve on salad plates lined with crisp greens.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Boil shrimp as you normally would and peel.
According to the size shrimp you use, cut accordingly:
Calabash shrimp:
Do not use.
Small:
Leave whole.
Medium:
Cut in half.
Large:
Cut in 3 pieces.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Wash and drain beans.
Put in large kettle with 6 cups water. Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Add 2 1/2 quarts water, bring to a boil, cover and simmer 2 hours or until beans are mushy.
Add margarine, potatoes, celery, onion, garlic and 3 teaspoons salt.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add more water if necessary to make a thick soup, then add pepper and more salt if necessary.
Sprinkle parsley over each serving of soup when ready to serve.
Yields 4 1/2 quarts.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: In a double boiler or large saucepan, combine sugar and flour. Add eggs and 1/2 quart milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture coats spoon.
Remove from heat, cool slightly; add vanilla and enough milk to fill freezer can.
Freeze according to directions.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Layer fruits in large bowl as given.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let set 5 minutes. Add salt, sugar and melted shortening. Add 3 cups flour. Beat well.
Add egg and 3 more cups sifted flour. Knead well and let rise before making into rolls.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Mix noodles and meat sauce.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: chicken in foil
directions: For each serving, place a half chicken breast on a piece of heavy duty foil.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Place 6 mushrooms on each breast and dot with 3 pats of butter.
Seal airtight.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
These may be frozen ready for the oven.

title: orange bread loaf
directions: To Prepare Orange Peel:
Peel oranges and chop 1 1/2 cups of orange peel.
Put peel into saucepan with 1 cup of water.
Boil 3 minutes.
Do this two more times.

title: no bake chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well with electric mixer or pie will be lumpy. Cook in a microwave on high for about seven minutes, stirring frequently until mixture thickens. Cool. Pour into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or more before serving.

title: macaroni and beef casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown hamburger, bell pepper, onion and mushrooms, drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, simmer on low heat. While sauce is simmering, cook macaroni in large pot, drain.
Pour sauce over macaroni; mix well.
Place mixture in casserole dish. Cover with cheese.
Place in oven just long enough to melt cheese. Serve with salad and fruit.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Combine cake mix, egg and butter.
Press into greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and cream cheese; blend well.
Pour on top of cake mixture. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Cut into squares to serve.
Sprinkle the top with cinnamon after it comes out of the oven for decoration.

title: knorr spinach dip
directions: Mix soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Stir in spinach, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover; chill 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: big wheel loaf
directions: Take meat out of freezer and soak in water 24 hours.
The next day, pour the water off and cover again with water, adding 2 tablespoons vinegar to every 4 cups of water and soak another 24 hours.
The third day, pour off water; wipe the meat off well and score about 1 inch deep all over.
Season with lots of salt and pepper and completely cover with butter, pushing it down into the cuts.
Top with brown sugar.
Pour red wine over the meat to make about an inch of liquid in the pan.
Cook very slowly in a 325° oven until black.
Baste every 15 minutes for the first two or three hours of cooking.

title: colorful stuffed peppers
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine broth, onions, corn, carrots, oregano and garlic.
Bring to a boil over medium heat. Stir in rice. Reduce heat to low. Cover pan and simmer until rice has absorbed all liquid, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Fluff with fork.
Lightly stir shredded cheese and peas into rice. Divide the mixture among peppers.
Mound tops slightly. Top with sliced cheese.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick spray. Add peppers. Cover loosely with foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 187 calories and 1 gram fat.

title: chicken with creamy broccoli rice
directions: In large skillet melt butter or oil over medium heat.
Brown chicken, 3 minutes each side.
Remove from skillet.
Combine soup, milk and pepper in same skillet.
Stir in
broccoli and carrots. Return chicken to skillet.	Bring to boil, cover and simmer for 20 minutes until chicken no longer is pink and veggies are tender crisp, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Melt cheese and margarine in top of double boiler.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Arrange in 2-quart casserole starting with broccoli first, then melted cheese and margarine and Ritz crackers. Finish with the Ritz crackers on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: cancun crab
directions: Saute red pepper and onion in butter.
Mix with crab, eggs, bread crumbs, mayonnaise, mustard, pepper, cayenne and Tabasco. Scoop onto English muffin halves in the following order:
English muffin, tomato slice, scoop of crab mixture and Swiss cheese slice.
Place on baking sheet.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Wash and shred cabbage.
Bring sugar, ketchup and vinegar to a boil; pour over cabbage.
Mix well.
Goes great with barbecue pork, chicken or beef.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender.
Drain well and mix with mayonnaise, butter, egg and sugar.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour in lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Crush stuffing and brown in butter.
Add pecans and cover top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: beef macaroni casserole
directions: Set oven at 300°.
Partially cook macaroni; drain and set aside.
Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Add to macaroni; mix in olives, mushrooms, soup, Worcestershire and garlic.
Stir to mix well.
Put in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish; add grated cheese on top.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spiced cranberry cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove spices and lemon with slotted spoon.
(Can be made in a large coffeepot.)

title: layered finger jello
directions: Mix flavored jello, 1 tablespoon gelatin and boiling water and let harden in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: raspberry-applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce just to boil.
Add gelatin and mix well.
Stir in raspberries.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch mold.
Chill until set. Serves 6.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Barely cook vegetables; drain and mix with mayonnaise that has been mixed with vinegar and Beau Monde.
Chill overnight.
Toss with 1 to 2 heads torn lettuce just before serving.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Remove squash from package and place in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave at High for 10 to 12 minutes. Turn bowl once.
Drain, if necessary.
Set aside.
Place bacon on rack.
Cover with paper.
Microwave at High 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain and crumble bacon, reserving drippings in baking dish.
Set bacon aside.
Stir onion into reserved drippings.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave at High for 1 to 2 minutes or until onion is tender.

title: maine coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream, then dry ingredients, then vanilla.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased pan, 9 x 13-inch.

title: apricot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place apricots in saucepan; cover with warm water and let stand 30 minutes.
Drain.
Cut into small pieces with scissors.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in water, orange rind and juice.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture and stir until well blended.
Add apricots and nuts; mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Let stand for 20 minutes before baking at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Grease tube pan with shortening and dust with flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until top springs back.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Melt margarine.
Add sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture gradually, mixing well.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into squares.

title: microwave hot fudge pudding cake
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together the 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa powder and baking powder.

title: swedish pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon salt in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Brown meat slowly on both sides in skillet.
Stick cloves into onions.

Add onions to meat along with the carrots, celery, the 1/3 cup water, corn syrup and anchovies. Cover and simmer about 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Transfer meat to serving platter and keep meat warm while preparing gravy.

title: kid's easy microwave fudge
directions: Mix thoroughly the sugar and cream in large microwavable bowl (mixture will boil up).
Microwave for 13 minutes on High.
Remove from microwave.
Add butter, vanilla and 1 cup pecans.
Beat a few strokes and drop by tablespoons on foil.
Do not put on waxed paper.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Combine cheeses, broccoli, mushrooms and herbs in food processor or chop coarsely.
Add cottage cheese just to blend.
Add more seasoning if desired.
Oil flat bottomed casserole large enough to hold rolled lasagna in one layer.
Pour 1/2 inch of the spaghetti sauce on bottom of casserole.
Halve lasagna noodles. Spread each with herb cheese mixture.
Roll up and place seam side down in casserole.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan.
Cover with foil.
Bake covered with foil 20 minutes in a 350° oven, then uncover and bake until brown and bubbly, about 20 minutes more.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 75 g, protein 27 g, fat 9 g, calories 494.

title: salmon mold
directions: In double boiler, melt cream cheese and soup.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in mold.
Serve with Escort crackers.

title: "super duper" chicken paprika
directions: Saute onion in oil and remove.
Brown chicken in oil in skillet.
Sprinkle cooked onion, paprika, salt and hot water over chicken.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 50 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to platter.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Debone and chop.
Cook potatoes and onions in chicken broth.
Add water as needed.
Cook pork and beef in skillet to remove grease.
Mash the potatoes.
Put all ingredients in large cooker and add water as needed.
Let simmer approximately 2 hours, stirring often.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix beef, sausage, bread, eggs, garlic, onion and salt.
Shape into bite size balls and roll in flour.
Brown in oil (small amount).
Add soup and simmer.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips and chop onion and garlic.
Saute in butter until chicken is lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch and cook 1 minute.
Add broth, sliced carrot, lemon juice and salt.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in pea pods until they separate.
Add parsley and rice.
Cover; remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Serve with egg rolls and a fresh fruit salad.

title: nighty-nite cookies
directions: Beat 2 egg whites stiff.
Fold in 2/3 cup sugar and pinch of salt.
Fold in 6 ounce package chocolate chips and 1/2 cup nuts.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Pour in strawberries with juice, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into large, flat casserole.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream evenly over the mixture.
Then gently spoon rest of gelatin mixture. Refrigerate.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Salt and brown the chicken.
Remove chicken; pour off all but enough cooking oil to brown the onion.
Then add the other ingredients.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Pour over the browned chicken in
a large pan.
Bake in oven at 250° for about 3 hours. Turn occasionally.
This is enough sauce for about 20 pieces of chicken.

title: white bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, salt, sugar and yeast; blend well.
Heat water and margarine to 125°.
Add water to flour and blend until moist.
Beat 3 minutes on medium.
By hand, stir in 4 1/2 to 5 cups flour until dough pulls clean.
Knead in 1/2 to 1 cup flour until elastic, about 12 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl with plastic wrap and towel.
Let rise until double in size (1 hour). Punch down to remove air.
Shape into ball and rest covered 15 minutes.
Shape into loaves and let rest 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugars and pudding.
Mix in large bowl.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture, then oats.
Batter will be stiff. Drop by rounded measuring teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets about 2-inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread cocktail sauce over the mixture; spread baby shrimp over sauce and top with oregano and a few parsley flakes.

title: california hot chicken salad
directions: Toss with fork the chicken, celery, almonds, pimento and mayonnaise blended with lemon juice, grated onion and seasonings. Fill a shallow greased casserole or individual ramekins.
Mix grated cheese and potato chips. Sprinkle over salad mixture. Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for about 30 minutes.
If using a casserole, it should be heated through and lightly browned.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Lightly mix beef, eggs, deviled ham, bread crumbs, salt, dry mustard and hot pepper sauce.
Shape into meatballs about 3/4 inch in diameter.
Arrange on jelly roll pans or other shallow pans. Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: quick, easy and healthy pasta sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients together in a pot.
Cook 1 pound of your favorite pasta.
When pasta is done, drain water halfway.
Pour sauce into macaroni.
Mix and serve.

title: whole wheat drop biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix liquid ingredients with salt, so salt has time to dissolve while you mix the flour and baking powder.
Add wet ingredients to dry and stir until just moistened. With ice cream scoop, scoop dough into balls in a 9-inch pie pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a light golden brown.

title: candy pie
directions: Put marshmallows and milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until marshmallows melt, stirring constantly.
Break candy bars into pieces and put in marshmallow mixture.
Continue over low heat until candy bars are melted; let cool.
Beat whipping cream with mixer until stiff.
Blend with chocolate mixture and pour in crust.
Chill.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: After peppers are prepared, put in pot with salt water to barely cover peppers.
Cook 10 minutes.
Cook 1/4 cup rice in same water.
Brown 3/4 pound ground meat in pan with onion and salt. Mix rice with meat.
Lay peppers, cut side up, in casserole dish. Stuff with rice and meat mixture.
Pour 1 small can tomato sauce over peppers.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: rice seafood casserole
directions: Cook rice, then saute it in 4 tablespoons of butter.
Add celery, green pepper and onion.
Prepare white sauce with remaining butter, flour and milk; cook and when cool, add mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix the shrimp, crabmeat and tuna into the white sauce.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Heat just to melt first 3 ingredients. Add cornflakes. Mix. Drop by spoonful on wax paper. Cool. Store in airtight container. Makes 4 to
5 dozen.

title: glazed stuffed cornish hens
directions: Truss birds if putting on spit.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk, corn syrup and salt, without stirring, until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Pour into buttered pan and when firm, cut in squares.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out water.
Mix all together.
Serve with a round rye loaf of bread hollowed out and dip put inside loaf or serve with party rye slices.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Add salt and pepper and drain.
Add green beans and soup.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes while hot.
Add milk and egg.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon over hamburger mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Brown on both sides for about 5 minutes.

title: date-nut pudding
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt, then stir in the nuts.
Mix soda into the dates, then pour boiling water over them.
Cream the butter until fluffy.
Add the sugar; cream again, then beat in the egg.
Add the flour mixture; mix thoroughly, then stir in the soaked dates.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan and bake for 1 hour.
Cool on a rack, then turn out and cut into squares.
Serve with any pudding sauce.

title: salsa dip
directions: Using a 13 x 9-inch pan, spread cream cheese across the bottom.
Layer refried beans (optional).
Layer on salsa sauce. Mix cheeses together and layer on top.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: play dough
directions: Cook all ingredients about 4 minutes.
Let cool about 5 minutes.
Knead dough 30 seconds.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Mix beef, onion and seasonings.
Shape into balls.
Place in skillet and cover with water.
Cook until water is almost gone. Mix water and soup.
Pour over meatballs and simmer for 15 minutes or until thick.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Stir together and cook until mixture turns to a soft ball in cold water or 240° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Coats about one quart of nuts of your choice.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: flo's emerald forest shredded potato bake
directions: Peel about 8 large potatoes.
Shred into cold salted water. Parboil until almost done.
Stir bottom of pan to keep from scorching.
Drain.
Place into large mixing bowl to mix.
Add butter, Parmesan cheese, onions, salt and pepper.
Place in baking pan.
Top with crushed seasoned potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 16.

title: artichokes
directions: Peel the artichokes until you reach the tender part.
Cut the big part of the remaining leaves.
Clean the main part of the artichoke all around and all the inside (feather line).
Put in the casserole the flour, lemon juice and part of the beef flavor; dissolve in the mixture the flour.
Put in all the other ingredients except the peas.
Pour the remaining beef flavor in; stir gently.
Let boil for about 1 1/2 hours on medium-low to medium heat (and watch it).
Five to ten minutes before the end of the boiling, put in the casserole the sweet peas, which first must be washed and drained from the cans water.
You can put more lemon juice in if you like it lemony and also more dill, which gives much needed flavor to the dish.
Add more hot water if needed. Add more flour if you want the sauce to be thicker.
A medium thickness is best.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: Mix milk, egg and spices in medium bowl.
Dissolve gelatine in water and let rest 1 minute in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until dissolved and melted.
Add milk mixture and cook until thick, about 5 minutes.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Put in graham cracker crust and chill.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Chop mushrooms finely unless it is desired to strain the soup. Melt butter in saucepan; fry mushrooms for 5 minutes, stirring to prevent their discoloring.
Stir in the flour and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove the pan from the heat and gradually add water and milk.
Bring to the boil and cook until soup thickens.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients together and cut in Crisco.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Mix, knead, roll and cut.
Allow 10 minutes to rise.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Cook onions 10 minutes in water with salt and sugar. Drain; add butter. Mix cornstarch with milk. Add to onions. Cook until thick. Put in a baking dish and top with buttered Ritz cracker crumbs. Brown in oven at 350 degrees.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins and let potatoes cool.
Peel potatoes and shred coarsely.
In saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Stir in shredded cheese.
Stir occasionally until almost melted. Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onions and seasonings. Pour over potatoes and fold in.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with 2 teaspoons of butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: In casserole, layer of beans, layer of hamburger, layer of onions.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
On top sprinkle brown sugar and pour over catsup.
Lay on strips of bacon.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup of milk in double boiler.
Mix cake mix with oleo and 1/3 cup milk.
Put half of cake mix in floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 3 to 6 minutes until firm enough to hold remaining half.
Spread chocolate chips and pour on caramel.
Add last half of cake mix.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rice and okra
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; cook about 1/4 cup of rice and add onion.
Pour some of the fat from the bacon in a frying pan and add the okra.
Cook until it is done.
Add the rice and onion and let simmer for awhile.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour, mixing well.
Add butter, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Pour mixture into pastry shell. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat well.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) greased cake pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until done.
Frost with cream cheese or vanilla frosting.

title: alba's baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain well. Cut bacon in small pieces and brown with the onion; drain well. Place everything in a crock-pot and stir well. Cook on low for approximately 4 hours or until flavors are blended. Serves 8.

title: veggie fry
directions: Fry all ingredients in oil. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: crab canapes
directions: Cut 4 rounds from each slice of buttered bread with a small cookie cutter or glass.
(Plastic medicine cup is ideal.)
Place rounds on a cookie sheet and bake in a 400° oven for about 6 minutes; cool.
May store in a plastic bag, sealed.
Combine crab, cheese, ketchup, onion and lemon juice.
Mix well and chill.
Just before serving, spread crab mixture on each toasted round and place on a serving tray.

title: chicken bake
directions: Mix chicken, soup and broccoli together.
Place in cake pan. Top with Stove Top stuffing.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: christmas favorite fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in large kettle.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly with rubber spatula or wooden spoon, until soft ball but firm ball stage.
Will take 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove from heat, beating until very thick and creamy. Be sure the gloss is gone and candy turns creamy.
Stir in nuts; turn into large 10 x 14 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares.
Keeps up to 6 weeks; will improve with age.
Makes 6 pounds.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar in boiler. Add the cocoa; stir. Add the milk. Add butter or margarine; stir. Put boiler on stove. Turn heat to low. Cook until starts to boil. Stir as it cooks. Boil about 2 to 4 minutes. Remove from stove. Add the peanut butter. Add the oats. Stir until well mixed. Add vanilla. Let cool. Drop on plate by spoon and refrigerate.

title: hearty minestrone soup
directions: In large stockpot, heat oil.
Saute onion and garlic for 1 minute.
Add carrots and celery; saute for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cabbage and saute for 2 minutes.
Add broth, sauce, water, beans and liquid and salt.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in pasta and simmer for 10 minutes.
During last 3 minutes, stir in peas.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel the apples and cut into thin slices.
Place apple slices in ungreased ovenproof dish (pie plate works well).
Put the remaining ingredients into a bowl and mix with a pastry blender until dry ingredients are somewhat blended and margarine is in small pieces.
Spread the topping over the apples and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: homestyle spaghetti sauce
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, heat corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes.
Serve over vermicelli.
Makes 3 cups.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place into a 9 x 12-inch glass pan.
Layer diced celery, diced onion, frozen peas (uncooked), green pepper, fried bacon (crumbled), Cheddar cheese and fresh parsley (chopped).
Mix the mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread on top.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
(Stays well; doesn't wilt.)

title: berry delicious lemonade
directions: Combine strawberries, lemon juice and sugar in blender and process until smooth.
Pour into a large pitcher; stir in cold water, ice cubes and, if desired, lemon slices.
Yields 7 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash. Add all ingredients and mix with mixer. Pour into casserole dish; sprinkle with topping.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour in a greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples. Pour melted shortening over mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips well.
Put crushed potato chips on top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot. Delicious!

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to directions.
Remove from heat and add eggs, margarine, seasoning salt, cheese and Tabasco.
Stir until all ingredients are melted and blended.
Pour into 3-quart buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. This may be frozen before baking.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: baked apples in orange juice
directions: Core and peel apples down halfway.
Fill apple centers with granulated sugar.
Place in deep baking dish and cover completely with orange juice.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.
Cool apples, turn upside-down in juice and refrigerate, covered, overnight or until completely chilled.
When ready to serve, place apple upright in individual serving dish.
Ladle small amount of juice over apple and top with mixture of sour cream and powdered sugar. Delicious for dessert or brunch.

title: baked scalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients and put in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: northern-style dumplings
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Pour in milk and add egg.
Mix only until flour is dampened.
Don't worry about lumps.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of boiling meat or fruit.
Cover tightly and steam for 12 minutes without raising cover.

title: ginger sole
directions: Combine yogurt, ginger and lime juice.
Spray baking pan.
Put fillet of sole in pan and top with yogurt mixture.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and carrots.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry cookie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pat out cookie dough to 10-inch circle on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake into golden brown.
Cool.
Stir powdered sugar into cream cheese.
Spread over cookie to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Spoon strawberry filling over cream cheese.
Cut into wedges.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato and mash real well.
Add salt.
When cool, add vanilla or any other flavoring you wish.
Add enough powdered sugar to make a stiff dough.
Knead; put into bowl and cover with a damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator 1 hour.
Shape into small balls.
Dip in melted chocolate and roll in ground nuts or coconut.

title: coney sauce
directions: Mix altogether in a large kettle.
Bring to boil; then simmer for 3 hours.

title: chili rebleno casserole
directions: Brown pork until crumbly and well done.
Add onions and saute until transparent.
Drain fat.
Add taco relish and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Beat together milk, eggs and flour; add cheese.

title: baked rigatoni
directions: Lightly saute onion and garlic in 5 tablespoons olive oil. Add tomatoes, red pepper, black pepper, basil and 1 teaspoon salt. Add stock and bring to a low boil.
Cook 40 minutes.
Drain pasta.
Toss with 3 tablespoons olive oil.
Add tomato sauce; toss. Add grated Monterey Jack cheese; toss.
Pour into large baking dish (greased). Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Arrange sliced olives on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly (25 to 30 minutes). Remove from oven and sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: hot crab meat spread
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Combine all ingredients, except almonds; mix well. Spread in ungreased 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle with almonds. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: homemade beets
directions: Wash beets.

Cook until tender. Peel and cut in chunks or slices. Put water, vinegar, sugar and salt in pan. Bring to boil. Put beets in until hot. Put in jars. Be sure to have jars and lids hot and do one jar at a time. You can cut the recipe down to make enough just for a meal.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package and drain.
Melt margarine and add 1/2 of Ritz cracker mixture.
Cube cheese and mix with broccoli.
Stir gently.
In casserole dish, layer until finished. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mash cookie slices evenly over pizza pan.
Bake according to directions and cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; spread over crust.
Arrange fruit in design.
Glaze.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix in Pyrex dish.
Cut 1/2 stick of oleo in pieces.
Put on top.
Cook for 50 minutes at 350° or until rice is done.

title: dandelion greens
directions: Gather greens before buds bloom.
Wash well and parboil until tender.
Drain well.
Fry in bacon grease.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low heat until seasonings cook in.

title: aunt marge's blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin
cups. Line bottom of cups with waxed paper.
In large bowl
mix
flour,
sugar, baking powder and salt with fork.
With pastry
blender
or
2 knives cut
in butter until mixture
resembles
fine
crumbs. Stir in nuts.
In small bowl beat eggs, milk
and vanilla with fork.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture just until flour is moistened. Gently
stir in blueberries.
Spoon
batter
into muffin cups. Bake 20 minutes or until
golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan and discard waxed paper.
Serve
warm or cool on wire rack to serve later.

title: quick-stir fish
directions: Saute onions in olive oil until onions are translucent; then mix
in
parsley.
Add
fish
and cook until it starts to flake apart
(about
10 minutes).
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water. Add
broth to fish; stir until fish is cooked, about 5 minutes. Serves 2 to 3.

title: carolina delights
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Continue boiling for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter; stir until well mixed.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper (or cookie sheet); allow to set. Cookies are best served while still warm.

title: rosemary roasted potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cut in half and arrange in shallow baking pan.
Drizzle with olive oil, turning potatoes to coat well. Sprinkle with seasonings.
Bake at 400°, stirring occasionally for 20 to 35 minutes, until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beefy crescent pie
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Mix beef, green beans, mushrooms, cheese and tomato sauce in a large mixing bowl.

title: (kids) 5 minute fudge
directions: In a medium saucepan, mix milk, sugar and salt.
Heat to boiling point, but do not boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add walnuts, marshmallows, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square cake pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: beets and horseradish
directions: Empty cans of beets; grate the beets.
Add horseradish, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Put in jars and refrigerate.
Serve with meat dishes.

title: okinawan doughnuts(andagi)
directions: Combine the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix well. Add the eggs and milk to the dry ingredients and mix only until the liquid is mixed with the flour mixture.
Do not overbeat. Drop with a teaspoon into deep fat and fry.
Drain on paper towels.

title: raisin crisscross cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix well the shortening, sugar, egg and flavoring.
Sift together and stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir in raisins.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts. Place about 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour, making crisscross pattern.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: french onion dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: In a bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening, margarine or butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in the center, add milk all at once.
Stir just until dough clings together.
On a lightly floured surface, knead gently for 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll or pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter, dipping cutter in flour between cuts.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Makes 10.

title: velvet almond fudge cake
directions: Chop almonds; place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes or until toasted.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup toasted almonds in well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream, water, oil and flavorings in large mixer bowl; mix well.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Fold in remaining almonds and chocolate chips.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake pulls away from side of pan.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack to cool completely.
Place on serving plate. Garnish with whipped topping.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salt water; do not overcook.
Place in a large casserole dish a layer of cabbage.
Mix all other ingredients except cheese together and pour 1/2 of soup mixture over cabbage. Repeat layers and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Before taken out of oven, sprinkle 1 cup of grated cheese and let melt.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, evaporated milk and powdered sugar. Mix glaze and strawberries.

title: braised turkey breast
directions: Rub turkey breast with oil.
Sprinkle with salt, sage, paprika and pepper.
Place onion and garlic in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place turkey breast on top.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour apple juice over turkey. Cover with foil
Insert meat thermometer through foil into thickest part of breast, making an opening so thermometer does not touch foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until thermometer registers 185°.
Transfer turkey to serving platter.
Serve with pan drippings.
Yields 14 to 16 servings.

title: linguine with no cook tomato sauce
directions: Mix all sauce ingredients in large bowl; let it stand for flavors to blend.
Cook linguine.
Add sauce.
Serve hot or cold.

title: no-fuss truffles
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, heat chips at 70% power for 1 minute; stir.
Microwave 10 to 20 seconds longer or until melted, stirring occasionally.
Cool to room temperature, about 30 minutes, stirring several times.
Fold in whipped topping.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper-lined baking sheets. Freeze for 1 1/2 hours or until firm.
Shape into balls; roll in almonds, crumbs or peanuts.
Refrigerate or freeze in an airtight container.
If frozen, remove from the freezer 30 minutes before serving.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: cornish hens with mushrooms
directions: Rinse hens in cool water and dry. Remove any visible fat. Sprinkle with pepper. Saute mushrooms in oil.
Add bread crumbs, pecans, onions, garlic, tarragon and pepper.
Combine milk and a tablespoon of vermouth.
Add to stuffing mixture to bind it. Loosely stuff hens and tie legs together.
Place hens, breast side up, on rack in baking pan. Roast at 350° for 45 minutes. Baste frequently with remaining vermouth.
Serving size:
1 hen. Exchanges:
4 meats, 1/2 bread and 1 fat.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls.
Chop up dried beef.
Save out 1/2 cup to roll cheese ball in.

title: mediterranean baked shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Butter a shallow 10-cup enameled cast-iron or glass baking dish. Heat the oil in a small frying pan. Add the scallions and cook over moderately high heat, stirring frequently, until softened, about 2 minutes. Add the garlic and cook, stirring for 1 minute longer. Spread the mixture in the prepared baking dish and arrange the shrimp on top. Sprinkle with the tomato and feta. In a bowl, beat the eggs with the dill, hot pepper sauce, salt and black pepper. Beat in the cream. Spoon the custard over the shrimp. The shrimp should be at least halfway covered with the custard. Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese. Bake for 17 minutes, until the custard is set and the shrimp are cooked through. Let the casserole stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and peanut butter.

Melt margarine. Stir into peanut butter mixture and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt Hershey bar. Spread over peanut butter mixture. Refrigerate 1/2 hour. Cut into squares and return to refrigerator.

title: pasta jambalaya
directions: In microwave, cook separately the sausage, chicken, onions and peppers (not quite tender).
Add cooked ingredients to kettle containing remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook fettucine until tender; drain.
Eat and enjoy!

title: grandpa's quick chili
directions: Brown hamburger in 1/2 gallon size saucepan.
Drain off grease and turn low heat.
Add tomato juice and each can of other ingredients.
Add diced onion and garlic powder (1/2 teaspoon). Turn on medium heat (do not overcook).
Season to taste with chili powder.

title: ground beef and spanish rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and pepper.
Salt to taste; drain.
Heat rice and mix with beef.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and pepper. Combine beet liquid and vinegar.
Slowly blend into cornstarch mixture. Place over medium heat and bring to boil. Boil 1 minute. Add beets and heat through. Yields 2 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on box; drain and cool.
Cook macaroni; will be 1 1/2 cups when cooked (use all).
Cool.
Mix all ingredients and set aside.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Put on crust.
Dot with butter.
Use enough milk to moisten.

title: bagel bites
directions: Mix the cream cheese until creamy.
Add the Worcestershire sauce and the dried onions.
Chop the ham into little pieces and add to mixture.
Stir.
Spread on the bagels and cut into bite size pieces.
(Cut like you would a pie.)

title: broccoli casserole
