directions: Mix broccoli with 1/3 of onion rings and place in a casserole. Then layer Rice-A-Roni, onion soup mixed with water, Cheez Whiz and remaining onion rings.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems of mushrooms and save.
Saute mushrooms in oleo and garlic.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in glass baking dish, 9 x 13-inch; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be doubled.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: In large frying pan, brown beef; drain.
Add in macaroni, onions, peppers and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Stir in tomato soup; cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Quick meal!

title: triple chocolate brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch pie plate.
In small mixer bowl, beat eggs; blend in sugar and butter.
In separate bowl, stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to egg mixture, beating until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Spread batter into prepared pie plate.
Bake 35 minutes or until set. Cool completely.
Cut into wedges.
Serve with ice cream.

title: salsa meat loaf
directions: Reserve 1/3 jar of salsa.
Beat eggs; add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in loaf pan.
Top with reserved salsa.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, white sugar and vanilla together.
Add in grapes (white or red) or a combination of the two.
Put in a serving dish.
Sprinkle on 1/3 cup brown sugar. Refrigerate.
Number of servings:
6 to 8.

title: caramel breakfast ring
directions: In an 8-inch round dish mix sugar, butter and water.
Heat for 1 minute and blend.
Stir in cinnamon and nuts.
Cut biscuits in quarters and mix with caramel mix.
Cook 2-3 minutes rotating dish 1/4 turn halfway through cooking time.
Rest 2-4 minutes. Pull apart to serve.

title: thelma lou's very chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine the crushed wafers and melted butter and press into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Use a drinking glass to press mixture into pan.
Set crust aside, you do not need to bake it.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix the soups together.
Add rice.
Dip chicken pieces in melted butter; lay on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pot roast
directions: Mix together ketchup and water.
Brown meat on both sides in frying pan or grill.
Put meat, vegetables and sauce in large pot. Bring to boil, then cook, covered, for 3 hours on low flame.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Bring milk to boil.
Add sugar and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add salt, egg and yeast.
Mix in 1 1/2 cups of flour and beat with spoon.
Add remaining flour.
Knead on floured board for 5 minutes.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Knead dough again for 3 minutes.
Use enough flour so dough does not stick to hands. While rising, cut medium size pepperoni stick into suitable size pieces.
Pour 1/2 can of tomato sauce and 2 tablespoons cooking oil over pepperoni.
Wrap each piece in dough.
Let rise in greased pan until doubled in size.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, flour and Seven-Up, a small amount at a time.
Add 2 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Mix well.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, beans and taco mix. Simmer.
Drain.
Break up lettuce.
Slice tomatoes.
Toss with meat mixture and Tostitos.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon; drain and save bacon grease.
Boil potatoes; add milk, cheese, sugar and crumbled bacon and bacon grease.
Thicken with flour.

title: veal and sauce
directions: Flour meat and brown in oil.
Drain mushrooms and save liquid. Add water to make 1 cup liquid.
Heat dissolved bouillon cube in liquid.
Pour over meat.
Combine tomato sauce, green pepper and mushrooms.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350°.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add chocolate chips, M&M's or anything you want.

title: mediterranean sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients except oil in blender at high speed. Add oil and blend until well emulsified.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Heat
oven
Melt
oleo
in
sheet
cake pan. Sprinkle brown sugar on top of oleo.
Arrange pineapple slices or crushed pineapple on top.
Mix yellow cake mix according to directions	on box.
Use pineapple juice for liquid in recipe. Bake for
to
minutes.
When done, cut around sides of cake and invert.
Let pan sit on top of cake for a few minutes to make sure all pineapple and topping comes loose.

title: fried banana honey
directions: Heat oil in wok.
Coat banana pieces in flour and then dip in beaten egg white.
Once oil is hot, put pieces of bananas into oil and fry until golden brown.
Put fried banana in plate and pour honey on top.
Sprinkle sesame seed over it and serve hot.

title: spicy stir-fry chicken with cashews
directions: (Note: Wear gloves to cut red chili peppers because they can burn the skin.)

title: aunt marilyn's chocolate cake
directions: Bake in sheet cake pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry refrigerator cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Prepare and bake cake according to package directions (follow Basic recipe).
Poke holes 1-inch apart in top of cake using handle from wooden spoon.
Puree thawed strawberries with juice in blender. Spoon evenly over top of cake allowing mixture to soak into holes.

title: mandarin chinese stir-fry
directions: Heat corn oil and stir-fry chicken with garlic powder to taste; remove.
Stir-fry broccoli, onion and other veggies for 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Return chicken to skillet.
Stir sauce over mix in pan and stir as it comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Serve with rice or Chinese noodles.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Arrange
lettuce,
cauliflower,
red onion and bacon in layers.
Dot on mayonnaise and sprinkle sugar on top.
Refrigerate overnight, then toss just before serving.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons soy sauce and sesame oil in dish.
Add chicken and turn until well coated.
Refrigerate until partially absorbed and turn.
Let stand 2 hours or longer.
Chop lettuce across the grain (3 1/3 cups), chop onions and refrigerate.
Mince garlic.
Add mustard, sugar, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, chicken broth, vinegar and 1/2 cup oil; put aside.
Heat 4 cups oil.
Add 1/3 of rice noodles; cook 30 seconds.
Turn and cook until they expand.
Remove and drain.
Repeat until noodles are gone.
Pat chicken dry; saute in 2 tablespoons oil until golden; cool and slice into strips.
Refrigerate.
Mix together and garnish with sesame seed and chopped green onion.

title: chicken curry
directions: In a large skillet or wok, saute chicken in olive oil until chicken is cooked through.
Remove chicken and set aside.

title: devonshire apple pie(makes 9-inch pie)
directions: In a large bowl mix sugars, flour, spices, lemon juice and salt.
Stir in cream and apples.
Spoon into pie shell.
Sprinkle with Streusel.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until apples are tender and topping golden brown.
Cool.
Serve with Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil fryers until tender with salt, pepper and several buttons of garlic.
Chop the pimento and grate the onion.
Chop parsley real fine. You won't have to grind up the chicken.
Mix all with salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Can be used for sandwiches, too.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat well; stir in chocolate chips and set aside.
Sift the next 5 ingredients together.
Add the remaining ingredients to the flour mixture. Beat until well combined.
Fill muffin cups lined with paper baking cups 1/3 full with chocolate batter.
Top with 1 tablespoon of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.
There is no need to ice, since the cream cheese mixture makes the topping.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: In large bowl, combine corn oil, vinegar, chopped parsley or cilantro, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salted water until fork tender, cool carrots. Alternate layers of carrots, bell pepper and onion in a dish. Make your marinade sauce with the remaining ingredients. Beat marinade sauce with mixer until completely smooth. Pour mixture over vegetable layers, refrigerate. This will keep for several weeks.

title: mom's overnight salad
directions: Layer in ingredient order into large glass salad bowl.
Mix together mayo and sugar; spread mayo/sugar mixture on top of other layers.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Mix well prior to serving. Should be eaten immediately.
Does not keep well.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Combine ingredients
until smooth. Drop by tablespoon in hot grease until brown.
Blot in paper towel.

title: chocolae slice 'n bake cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in Nestle Choco-Bake unsweetened baking chocolate flavor and vanilla extract.
Beat in egg and blend in flour mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts onto waxed paper.
Spread half the dough down center of nuts.
Lift up sides of waxed paper to shape dough into a log.
Wrap securely with aluminum foil.
Repeat with remaining 1/2 cup nuts and dough.
Chill in freezer up to 2 weeks.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and butter.
Melt over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add sweetened condensed milk and mix well.
In a medium bowl, combine chocolate mixture, vanilla and flour.
Add nuts and mix well. Mixture will
be very thick.
Use a measuring spoon and shape 1 tablespoon around each candy kiss.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6 or 7 minutes.
Do not overbake. Cool and drizzle melted almond bark over top.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Mix together.
Put in cupcake pan and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: bubble bread(child-approved)
directions: Cut each biscuit in half and roll each one into a ball.
Roll balls in melted butter.
Roll balls in cinnamon/sugar mix.
Place balls into loaf pan.
Put loaf pan in toaster oven at 375° or oven at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Turn loaf pan over into dish and enjoy!

title: beef-and-bean supper
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans; let soak overnight.
Drain beans; cover with water.
Cover and bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Baking Temperature: 250°.
Baking Time: 1 hour.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring 1/2 cup of water to a boil.
Add broccoli and onion.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender; do not drain.
Stir in soup, milk, cheese and red pepper.
Cook and stir about 4 minutes or until heated through.
Pass peanuts to sprinkle on top of soup, if desired.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: batter-up brownies
directions: Spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Pour onto wax paper.
Add baking powder and salt.
Stir to blend (I use a bowl). Melt shortening in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Remove; cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.
Yields 3 dozen bars.

title: spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach, wash and pat dry.
Tear into bite-size pieces.
Combine with pecans and strawberries.
Drizzle with Poppy Seed Dressing.
Toss and serve.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Combine butter with sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour to mixture, then add chips.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter honey roll
directions: Mix peanut butter, honey and dry milk together in a small bowl.
Roll into a ball.
Crush Wheat Chex on wax paper and roll ball through it.
Eat as is!

title: vegetable health salad
directions: Combine cabbage, celery, carrots, green pepper, pecans and onion in large bowl; mix well.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
Add lemon juice, mayonnaise and salt; mix well.
Pour over vegetables; mix well.
Pour into serving dish.
Chill until set.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: epicurean beef
directions: Combine beef, wine, consomme, salt, pepper and onions in casserole.
Mix bread crumbs with flour and stir into meat. Cover and bake in a slow oven (300°) for about 3 hours or until beef is tender.
Serve over rice or noodles of your choice with a tossed salad and fresh, hot French bread for a delicious, hearty "feel good" meal.
Makes 6 servings.

title: island broiled chicken
directions: Marinate overnight or for several hours, then barbecue.

title: curry dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Serve with assorted vegetables.

title: little shepherd's pies
directions: In a large skillet, over medium heat, saute onion and green pepper in oil for 5 minutes.
Add meat.
Cook and stir until meat loses its pink color, about 5 minutes.
Drain fat.
Mix in salt and pepper; set aside.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Drain cans of fruit (saving juice and set aside) for 2 hours. Mix all ingredients except for fruit.
Peel and cut apples and bananas; let sit in reserved juice for several minutes.
Remove from juice with slotted spoon and add to mixture along with drained fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: creole of sausage
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch slices.
Brown in large skillet or electric frypan with butter.
Add sliced peppers, onion, zucchini and eggplant.
Stir in stewed tomatoes.
Cover and cook down 1/2 hour or so.
Put in baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cover with sauteed mushrooms.
Place Mozzarella cheese on mushrooms.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
(Mushrooms may be omitted, if desired). Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly and browning, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: holiday vegetable casserole
directions: Drain all vegetables well.
Layer asparagus on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix peas and soup; put on top of asparagus.
Layer water chestnuts on top.
Cover with grated cheese.
Cut white bread into strips (no crust).
Dip into margarine or butter and place on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: dump cake
directions: Cook and cool pie crust.
Slice bananas in crust.
Mash an 8 ounce package of cream cheese and add cup of sugar and medium Cool Whip.
Mix well and pour over bananas.
Top with blueberry pie filling.

title: shirley's strawberry slush
directions: Dissolve 1 1/2 cups sugar in 2 cups boiling water; add 1 (6 ounce) can frozen orange juice and 3 cans water.
Set aside.
Mix 12 ounces apricot nectar, 3 diced bananas, 1 (20 ounce) can crushed pineapple, 1 (10 ounce) frozen strawberries and 2 tablespoons lemon juice in blender; add to orange juice mixture.
Makes 24 to 30 servings.
Keep in freezer.
Stir several times as slush freezes. To serve, mix 1/2 gallon slush and 1/2 glass 7-Up.

title: shrimp or crawfish etouffee
directions: Simmer onions in butter until wilted.
Note:
Do not use cast-iron pan or skillet!
Add spices and bell pepper.
Note:
Go easy on the salt!
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth and bring to a simmer (mixture will thicken).
Add shrimp or crawfish and cook until done (about 10 minutes).
Serve over rice and enjoy!
Serves 4 hungry people or 6 people on a diet!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all the ingredients together.

title: raisin-nut delight drops
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs, then vanilla. Mix and sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mix.
Stir in nuts and/or raisins (a total of 1 1/2 cups).
Drop by spoonfuls onto oiled cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 10 to 15 minutes.

title: frontier jerky
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients except meat.
Stir well.
Place meat 3 or 4 layers deep in a glass, stoneware, plastic or stainless steel container, spooning liquid mixture over each layer.
Cover tightly.
Marinate 6 to 12 hours in the refrigerator, stirring occasionally and keeping the mixture tightly covered.
Lay on greased racks.
Place in 160° oven for 4 to 5 hours.
Turn oven down to 130° and continue to bake until dry.
Makes 1/4 pound jerky.

title: rice gumbo(quick and easy)
directions: Combine Minute rice and chicken gumbo soup, adding 1 can water.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add cheese and allow to stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Add shrimp, broken into halves. Reheat and serve.

title: no roll sugar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Press with sugared glass.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Combine grated carrots and raisins; add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Add coconut and/or pineapple, if desired.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken breasts in salted water to cover until meat is tender.
Remove from broth; reserve broth and cut chicken from bone and return to broth.
Combine flour, melted butter and milk; mix well.
Roll out on lightly floured board and cut into thin strips.
Drop into hot chicken broth.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: creme de cacao pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatine onto cold milk, let stand 5 minutes.
Melt butter, stir in 1/3 cup sugar and cocoa.
Add gelatin mixture. Blend well, stir in beaten egg yolks.
Blend well.
Heat until mixture is hot, do not boil.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add 1/3 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Pour into creme de cacao mixture.
Fold until mixed.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop beef real fine; mix half of it with cheese, onion, Accent and sauce.
Form ball and roll in remainder of beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil. Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat, about 1 minute or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at one time.
Continue beating until smooth.
Drop dough by scant 1/4 cupfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Cool away from draft.
Cut off tops.
Pull out any filaments of soft dough.
Mix pudding by directions and fill puffs.
Replace tops and dust with confectioners sugar.
Chill and serve.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix together by hand; add 1/2 tsp. onion powder during mixing; for thinner dip add more mayonnaise.
Excellent with chicken crackers or ripple chips.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Prepare cake as instructed on box.
Let cool completely.
Take handle of a wooden spoon and poke holes over top of cake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Saute onion in oleo.
Add celery seed.
Combine all ingredients in a casserole except cheese. Spread Cheez Whiz over top.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make a sauce of all ingredients except potatoes; pour over potatoes and stir slightly.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: steak marinade by babinic
directions: Soak steaks in first 5 ingredients.
While charcoal grilling, baste with butter or peanut oil; add dry Vermouth and mix until creamy.
Add garlic, onion powder and salt and pepper.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans at the bottom of a large casserole dish. Brown and drain the hamburger meat; spread layer over refried beans.
Open both jars of salsa and spread over the meat.
Top the casserole with the cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with sour cream.
Eat the dip with chips.
Enjoy.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine flour and pecans.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: "food for the gods"
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Mix all ingredients except whipping cream. Bake in a greased 9 X 9 baking dish for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool and break up. Add one pint of whipped cream and fold together. Add several drops of vanilla and a little sugar to the whipped cream. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: "orange" chicken
directions: Makes enough marinade for 20 pieces of chicken.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Cover and marinate for up to 2 days for full flavor.
Grill chicken until done.

title: chicken soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large kettle.
Bring to boil. Cover and simmer over low heat for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add water, if needed.
Cool.
Remove bones.
Chill, then discard fat.
Reheat and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach appetizer pinwheels
directions: Combine spinach, cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, pimento and nutmeg, mixing until well blended.
Unroll dough; separate into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations together to seal.
Spread with spinach mixture.
Roll up, starting at short end.
Cut each roll into 8 slices.
Place cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 32 appetizers.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and softened cream cheese until creamy. Gradually add Tang, taste while mixing to see how tart you want it. Pour into pie shell, chill and slice.

title: washday soup
directions: Put navy beans in a big pot of salted water to soak overnight. Put on to cook about six in the morning, the same time you start your wash water.
Boil with bacon or ham.
Let cook on low burner and check in between loads of wash.
Add your onion at daylight before you hang out the overalls.
About 9 o'clock, have a quick cup of coffee and dump 1/2 cup in the beans.
Add carrots at bleach time, around eleven.
Serve at noon with soda crackers or cornbread and slaw you made the night before.

title: banana-split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (no sides).
Mix eggs, confectioners sugar and butter at medium speed until creamy.
Spread over crust. Chop and layer bananas, crushed pineapple, Cool Whip, cherries (place in rows) and chopped walnuts.
Drizzle with Hershey's syrup.
Refrigerate 1 day in advance.

title: peach pudding
directions: In bowl, cream stick of butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add 1 cup flour plus 2 teaspoons baking powder.
Spread over peaches in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add 1 cup hot water.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy italian popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn and set aside for later.
Melt the butter over low heat and mix in the Parmesan cheese.
Then use a big spoon to drizzle it over the popcorn.
Sprinkle just a bit of onion salt and pepper on and then maybe just a couple of shakes of Parmesan if you have any left.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: Melt butter in square cake pan (9-inch).
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour condensed milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good warm or cold.
Also, good with ice cream on top.

title: 5 bean bake
directions: Drain the white limas, kidney beans and green limas. Any kinds of beans may be used.

title: prune spice cake(extremely rich)
directions: Put baking soda in buttermilk.
Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, cloves, cinnamon, salt, buttermilk and prunes.
Add nuts and coconut.
Beat well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie shells (2) and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Trim excess fat from leg of lamb.
In the roasting pan, place the side of lamb, having some fat, facing up.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Roast for 30 minutes per pound.
After 1 hour, baste with part of Port wine. Repeat, basting with remaining wine, 1/2 hour later.
Peel onions and chop.
Combine onions and mushrooms with the liquid.
About 2 hours before roast is done, place onion-mushroom mixture on top of roast.
Continue roasting, basting with onion-mushroom mixture several times.
Plan to have roast done about 20 minutes before serving time to allow for easier slicing.

title: spaghetti pie(low-fat)
directions: Two hours ahead:
Line a colander with a coffee filter or 2 layers of paper towels; pour 12 ounces of plain nonfat yogurt in the colander.
Put colander in bowl.
Place in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours.
Use yogurt that's left in top; discard liquid that drains beneath.
(This should yield 1 cup or 8 ounces of thickened yogurt.)

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, mix oil, sugar, eggs, pumpkin and water.
Mix all dry ingredients; add to liquid.
Blend well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: barbecue corn-on-the-cob
directions: Put barbecue sauce and butter in saucepan and heat until butter melts.
Husk corn and remove silks.
Place each ear of corn on a heavy piece of foil; sprinkle each ear with salt and pepper. Scatter onions on each ear.
Pour 1/4 cup barbecue sauce on each ear.
Fold foil securely around each.
Cook outside on grill or in a 400° oven about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet gherkins
directions: First day:
Cover all cucumbers with boiling water.

title: east turkey divan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange turkey in an ungreased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch dish.
Top with hot broccoli; cover with cheese. Stir together milk and soup; pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with onion rings and bake 5 minutes longer. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mom's night off
directions: Freeze ingredients together.
Use half the slush and half Sprite or Seven-Up in a glass.
Drink and enjoy.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine over
low heat in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; sprinkle brown sugar over butter.
Arrange pineapple slices in bottom
of
pan.
Decorate
with
cherries
and
pecan halves. Prepare
cake
mix
according to package directions; pour over pineapple.
Bake
in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes. Invert pan
immediately
after taking from oven; let set a few minutes before removing pan.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Season chicken breasts with garlic, onion, salt and pepper. Simmer 1 hour, debone and drain.
Mix mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Add grapes, water chestnuts and chicken.
Mix well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the shortening and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir dry ingredients into shortening and sugar.
Mix well.
Add mashed bananas and blend well.
Add nuts, stirring gently.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until brown (do not overbake).
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes before removing from pan. Makes 1 loaf.

title: impossible chicken-vegetable pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables and cheese.
Spoon evenly into lightly greased pie plate.

title: peanut butter-chocolate fudge
directions: Combine the sugar and cocoa in a saucepan and stir in the cream.
Bring to a boil and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and peanut butter and beat until smooth.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper and cool.

title: hot spiced chocolate
directions: Combine all milk, 4 cinnamon sticks, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves in a saucepan.
Stir with a wire whisk.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated (do not boil).
Remove from heat.
Discard cinnamon sticks.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into individual mugs and top each with marshmallows.
Garnish with fresh cinnamon stick.

title: pistachio almond pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl. Blend; then beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 4 minutes. Pour into 10-inch fluted tube pan that has been greased and floured or sprayed with Pam pure vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan. Do not underbake.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; finish cooling on rack.

title: icebox fruit cake(club member: christy hosey)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pack tight in 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.

title: swedish pea soup with pork
directions: Soak yellow peas in just enough water to cover them and add 1 tablespoon salt per 3 3/4 cups water.
Leave for about 12 hours, then drain off the liquid.
Place pork knuckle or pork shoulder in a large saucepan.
Cover with water.
If you are using shoulder, put on the peas and meat at the same time.
Bring the meat to a boil and skim.
Peel and add onion, cut in slices.
Boil for about 1 hour, then add the drained peas.
Simmer over low heat until the peas are soft and the meat tender.
This will take another 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Skim thoroughly.
(If the meat is cooked before the peas, remove it and keep warm.)
Add crumbled thyme or marjoram towards the end.
Season with salt, if necessary.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's hickory nut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter for cake.
Add eggs; beat for 2 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients together lightly with a fork.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Make frosting.

title: grandmother's icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers and place in a large bowl. Add nuts, cherries, raisins and spices to crackers.
Put milk and marshmallows in a large pot and heat slowly (do not boil) until marshmallows are melted. Stir to keep from sticking.
Pour into cracker mixture and mix with hands.
(Make sure nuts and cherries are not knotted up.)
Put this into a casserole dish lined with wax paper.
Press mixture until solid.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Decorate with nuts and cherries.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased casserole dish.
Place cheese on top of chicken.
Mix soup and milk, pour over chicken. Sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be prepared and frozen to cook at later time.

title: irish bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
In a large bowl, mix together dry ingredients.
Add raisins.
Combine the dry ingredients with the cream mixture; mix all together.
Pour in a greased loaf size pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange juice jello salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello; stir until jello is dissolved. Add frozen juice, then the pineapple and nut meats.
Chill until set.
It is a tart salad, which is very refreshing.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan.
Stir together the chocolate chips, marshmallows and nuts; set aside. In large, microwave-safe bowl, place butter.
Microwave at High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until melted.
Add sugar, vanilla and eggs, beating with spoon until well blended.
Add flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; blend well.
Spread batter into prepared pan. Bake for 22 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chip mixture over top. Continue baking 5 minutes.
Cool completely.
With wet knife, cut into squares.

title: mrs. bruce's hot punch
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Let red hots melt before serving.
You can float an orange with cloves in it on top.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal and baking powder in a mixing bowl. In another bowl, combine corn, slightly beaten eggs, sour cream and jalapenos; add to dry mixture, stirring until all ingredients are moistened.

title: "jamie's" dip
directions: Brown beef.
Pour off grease.
Mix in chili.
Cut cheese in chunks to aid melting.
Combine until melted and mixed thoroughly. Serve hot.
Keeps well in fridge.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; add syrup mix, then add remaining ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: marie's easy and delicious pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients in pie pan and mix.
Don't over mix.

title: meat balls with broccoli
directions: Put broccoli in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix beef, 1 tablespoon of onions, carrot, salt, garlic, pepper and seasoned salt.
Shape into 16 small balls; put on broccoli.
Mix remaining onions and rest of ingredients.
Pour over and cover.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pasta and spinach salad
directions: Combine pasta, spinach, onions, tomato, and mushrooms.
Toss gently.
Pour 3/4 cup Basil Dressing evenly over salad. Toss. Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Serve immediately.

title: southern cornbread dressing
directions: Mix bread, raw eggs and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Have dressing soft, about the consistency of cake batter or thick soup. This is the secret of good dressing.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 baking dish for about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spring cottage cheese spread
directions: Mix cottage cheese with sour cream.
Add radishes, onion and salt; toss to mix well.
Mound on lettuce leaves.
Garnish with radish roses; surround with bread.
Makes about 2 1/3 cups.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Drain tomatoes well.
Toast enough bread for 1 cup cubes. Drizzle 1 tablespoon butter over cubes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake until bubbling in a 350° oven.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Separate egg yolks from whites.
Set whites aside to be used as meringue.
In a large bowl, add the egg yolks, condensed milk and grapefruit juice.
Mix until blended.

Pour into pie shell and bake for 15 minutes at 350° or until filling is no longer liquid. Beat the egg whites until stiff with electric mixer, gradually adding 2 or 3 teaspoons of sugar while beating.
Spoon meringue on top of cooked pie; bake until meringue is golden brown.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Heat the peanut oil in a skillet; add ginger and garlic and stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Add the vegetables, soy sauce, black bean sauce, chili sauce and vegetable stock.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add the sesame oil and the cornstarch, diluted with water, and give it one final stir.
Serve with jasmine rice or Oriental noodles.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Select crisp, fresh cucumbers; wash, but do not pare them. Slice crosswise in paper-thin slices.
Slice the onions thin and cut the peppers into fine shreds.
Mix the salt with the vegetables and bury pieces of cracked ice in the mixture.
Cover with a weighted lid and let stand 3 hours; drain thoroughly.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and salt in a 3 quart casserole or mixing bowl.
Loosely cover with lid or plastic wrap. Microwave on high for 3 - 4 minutes or until soft ball stage is reached.
Stir in marshmallows, nuts, milk, chocolate chips and vanilla extract.
Stir until marshmallows and chocolate chips are completely melted.
Pour into well greased
9 x 7 inch baking dish.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: caramel topped apple pie
directions: In saucepan, steam the apples three minutes in 1/4 cup water. Turn out on cookie sheet to cool quickly.
Arrange in 9-inch pastry lined pan.
Combine the next eight ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt in top of double boiler the milk and caramels.
Pour over top of pie and continue baking 10 minutes more.
Cool before serving.

title: hobos
directions: Form ground beef into patties.
Slice onions thickly.
Chop carrots and potatoes into bite-size pieces.
Place patty on large piece of aluminum foil.
Top with a slice of onion and enough carrots and potatoes for 1 person.
Add seasonings to your own taste and close the foil.
Wrap in another sheet of foil for added strength.
Place on the grill for 30 to 40 minutes.
You can use chicken or pork chops instead of ground beef.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Layer the cabbage, green pepper and onion. Add the sugar and let stand in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Bring to a boil the oil and vinegar.
Pour over the cabbage mix while very hot.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 2 hours, then mix. The longer it stands, the more crisp it gets.

title: pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to soft ball stage (238° to 240°), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir until mixture thickens, becomes creamy and cloudy and pecans stay suspended in mixture.
Spoon out on buttered wax paper, aluminum foil or parchment paper.
Makes 1 to 50 pralines, depending on size.
When using wax paper, be sure to buffer with newspaper underneath, as hot wax will transfer onto whatever is beneath.

title: bacon muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 medium muffin cups.
Mix baking mix, sugar, egg and water (or milk) with fork.
Beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Stir in bacon.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Sift together flour, 1/2 brown sugar and butter.
Mix in butter with your hands until a ball of dough is formed.
Pat dough into 9 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 minutes. Beat eggs.
Add corn syrup, 1/2 cup brown sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Stir in pecans.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: wedding day punch
directions: Freeze the pineapple and apple juices.
Take out of freezer 3 to 4 hours prior to mixing punch.
Put in a punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.

title: all-american snack
directions: In large mixing bowl or slow cooking pot (crock-pot), mix together pretzels, cereal and peanuts. Sprinkle with garlic salt, seasoned salt and cheese.

title: fish provencal
directions: Place fillets in skillet; almost cover with wine.
Put onion, tomato and lemon slices on fish.
Cover pan and poach until done. Remove when done to warm platter.
Thicken liquid in skillet. Pour over fish.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients until dissolved and marinate meat overnight.
Place a toothpick through the end of each strip. Place a layer of foil in oven to catch drippings.
Suspend strips from top oven rack.
Turn heat to 120° or lowest setting.
Allow oven door to stand slightly open so moisture will escape.
Heat strips 6 to 8 hours or until meat has turned dark and there is no moisture left.
Store in airtight container.
Will keep for 2 years.

title: giant pancake
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
In a mixing bowl, beat the eggs lightly with a rotary beater, then beat in the flour, milk and nutmeg.
Melt the butter over moderate heat in a heavy skillet with a heat-proof handle.
When the butter is hot, immediately pour in all the batter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown and puffed.
Sift the sugar over the pancake and return to the oven for 1 or 2 minutes.
Remove from the oven and sprinkle it with the lemon juice.
Cut into wedges and serve with fruit syrup, preserves, honey or maple syrup.
The pancake will puff while baking, but when taken from the oven it will fall (resembling a crepe).
Preparation time:
5 minutes; cooking time: 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: janah's surprise
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients until fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into molasses mixture, form in small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar; place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) about 15 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: german pasta
directions: Boil chopped potatoes, set aside.
Boil egg noodles according to package directions, omitting salt.
Steam chopped vegetables together; set aside.
Fry sliced sausage in pan with vegetables cooking spray.

Mix spaghetti sauce mixture according to package directions in saucepan, replacing butter with Butter Buds and using no salt added tomato paste instead of regular tomato paste. Add no salt added tomato sauce, boiled potatoes and garlic sausage.
To serve, place noodles on plate, layer with steamed vegetables and top with sauce.

title: maw maw's baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat on stove top, microwave or oven.
Serve with macaroni and cheese and hot dogs for a complete "Maw Maw Supper".

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Brown meat in hot oil; add mushrooms, rice, onion and soy sauce.
Continue to fry over low heat 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add the well beaten egg and continue to stir for another 5 minutes or until dry enough to be fluffy.
Add additional soy sauce, if you prefer a dark color.
Makes 6 or 8 servings.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Blend
all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for
2 minutes.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cherry tart
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread 2/3 of batter in 11 x 15-inch greased cookie sheet.
Spread on 1 can cherry pie filling.
Dot remaining batter on top and swirl around.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Drizzle on powdered sugar frosting while warm.

title: hot wassail
directions: Put cloves and cinnamon in a bag.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over leaves.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain. Mix beef, salt, pepper, onion, rice and egg together.
Add some filling to each cabbage leaf.
Fold over and fasten with toothpicks.
Put rolls in pot.
Pour tomato soup and water over rolls.
Cover and cook until done.
Cook in pressure canner 8 minutes after control jiggles for quick rolls.
Filling can be used for stuffed peppers.

title: double layer chocolate pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Spread onto bottom of crust.
Pour 2 cups milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk until well mixed.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Immediately stir in remaining whipped topping.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together turkey, rice, celery, soup, mayonnaise, juice, onion and seasonings.
Place half of this in casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese over top. Cover with sliced eggs, saving some slices for garnishing.
Top with remaining turkey mixture.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Add almonds, then potato chips and cook uncovered 20 minutes on High in microwave.

title: mixed sweet pickle
directions: *I use only 4 cups of sugar.

title: apple strudel
directions: Pat dough onto baking stone, making 2 rectangles (1 tube per rectangle).
Pinch seams together.
Sprinkle flour over dough. Peel, core and slice apples.
Chop into small pieces.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; remove 2 tablespoons for later.
Add sugar mixture, nuts, egg yolk and apples.
Spread filling down the middle of the dough.
Cut pats of butter and lay on top of the filling.
Make diagonal cuts on dough on each side.
Pull over to crisscross on top.
Brush with egg whites, then sprinkle remaining sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: grammie's granola
directions: Place oats in ungreased 2-quart utility dish.
Heat in microwave on Full power for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Add wheat germ, coconut, sesame seed, nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon to oats. Stir to blend.
Add oil, honey and vanilla to dry ingredients. Toss lightly until coated.
Cook in microwave for 3 minutes on High or until heated through.
Stir twice during cooking.
Add chocolate chips; cook in microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes. Press granola firmly against bottom of the dish.
Cool, cut into bars and store in a tightly covered container in the refrigerator.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Put in baking dish and crumble potato chips over top.
Can mix the day before.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
It serves 8 to 10 people.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Use 9-inch baking pan. Spray pan with Pam cooking spray.
Tear chicken apart and place in pan.
Then in a large bowl, mix sour cream and soup together with a large spoon until it is nice and creamy.
Then spread on chicken in the pan.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and pour into a greased oblong cake pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° until a toothpick comes out clean, for about 1 hour.

title: parsonage potato soup
directions: Cook celery, onion, carrots, parsley flakes and bouillon cubes in water and margarine until nearly tender, approximately 25 minutes.

title: braised spicy spareribs
directions: Flour and season meat.
Brown in oil slowly.
While meat is browning, make sauce from ingredients.
Put browned meat into roasting pan.
Pour sauce over.
Add chopped onions and bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
After meat is roasted, remove from roaster with a slotted spoon to warm serving platter.
Keep warm.
Pour sauce into saucepan.
Skim off extra grease.
Bring sauce to boil and slowly add flour and water mixture to thicken as desired, stirring constantly.
Serve in a gravy boat with mashed potatoes.
Make an extra recipe of sauce for additional gravy. You can use other kinds of meat also.

title: company spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach well.
Cut out the stalks.
Tear the spinach into small pieces.
In a small bowl, combine the spinach, tomatoes, chopped onions, and green pepper strips.
Pour on dressing.
Serve.

title: peanut butter balls(quick and easy)
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until well blended.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes at 300° or until lightly browned.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Place ingredients (except beef) in a covered casserole. Microwave on High until cheese spread is melted, about 5 minutes, stirring once.
Add ground beef, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups of dip.

title: walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour; add baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture, alternating with milk. Add chopped walnuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch pans. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: frosted nut delight
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Fold in eggs and sifted dry ingredients.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Spread batter onto a baking sheet as thinly as possible.
Frost.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs by hand.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured oblong cake pan.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 300° oven.
Sprinkle cake with rows of marshmallows.
Increase oven to 350° and bake for 10 minutes longer, cool cake completely.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and dissolve well the boiling water and Jell-O. Add other ingredients, except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: ballard's farm sausage dressing
directions: For 18 to 20 pound turkey:
Mix all ingredients well. Refrigerate overnight.
Do not stuff until ready to bake turkey.

title: trifle
directions: Bake cake according to package.
When baked and still warm, prick with fork and add Kahlua to cake.
Break up cake, flatten in dish and pat down.
Add instant pudding to 1/2 whipped cream. Spread La Creme over cake; add more cake, cream and La Creme and top with whipped cream.
Place chipped chocolate on top of cream. Add cherry in center.
This is made in a special glass trifle dish.

title: date balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, beaten egg and dates.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies and mix well; let cool.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.
Place on waxed paper.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly mix shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, then add melted chocolate.
Sift together next 3 dry ingredients and blend into mix.
Drop by teaspoon into confectioners sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 12 to 15 minutes.

title: paula's cheese roll
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients until smooth.
Roll in chopped nuts (pecans) and shape in desired shape.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Toss vegetables (squash, onions and carrots) in a bowl to mix. Place in a greased 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Stir soup and sour cream together to mix well, then spread mixture over vegetables.
Top casserole with butter-coated stuffing and bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle pecans and coconut over bottom. Mix cake mix as directed. Pour over pecans and coconut. Mix cream cheese, oleo and confectioners sugar. Pour over cake. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350° or until done. Most of icing will sink into the cake batter while cooking. Makes cake super moist.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Brown meat and saute together with bell pepper and onion.
In 9 x 12-inch dish mix all ingredients together.
May want to add some of the hominy liquid.
Add a little salt and cayenne pepper. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashion rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in flat baking dish.
Place in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes with fork, carefully turning under the brown top and scraping the edges down.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cherry kolacky cookie
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese, milk and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolk.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Refrigerate until dough is thoroughly chilled, 4 hours or overnight.
Roll or pat out on a well-floured board to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with a cookie cutter into 2-inch rounds.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and make a depression with thumb or spoon in center of each round. Fill centers with scant teaspoon Solo cherry filling.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving.
Makes approximately 36.

title: crunch
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in egg and margarine. Sprinkle over fruit filling.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until brown on top.
Serve warm or cold with dap of Cool Whip topping.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend seasoning mix with sour cream and let stand in refrigerator for several hours before serving.
Serve with Fritos. This is a hot dip.

title: cheese potatoes in foil
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Slice potatoes on large piece of foil.
Add salt and pepper, bacon, onion and cheese. Slice butter over top.
Fold foil in drugstore fold.
Seal ends well.
Grill over coals for 1 hour, turning several times.

title: wheelstone soup
directions: The noodles in this soup are fragile.
You want to maintain the shape and color of them, so treat them kindly.
Keep them separate and add them to the soup as you need it.
Add 1 1/4 cups of cooked noodles to each quart of soup as needed.
Float 3 to 4 slices of zucchini on top of bowl of soup and suggest that the customer sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Place the cheese nearby, so it will be convenient.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ketchup, brown sugar and mustard.
After 40 minutes of baking, pour this topping on loaf and continue to bake.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tennessee light corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, salt and sugar.
Add melted butter and buttermilk.
Grease and flour 2 (9 5/8 x 5 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch) loaf pans.
Pour mixture into loaf pans and smooth top.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake an additional 40 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool before slicing.
Serve toasted with butter.
This can be sliced, wrapped and frozen.
You can bake in tube pan, greased and floured, at 350° for one hour.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together; bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix punch and pineapple juice well.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.
When ready to serve, add cold ginger ale. Mix and serve.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: honey fruit cookies
directions: Combine the flours, cinnamon, baking powder, ginger, nutmeg, soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
In mixer bowl beat butter or margarine 30 seconds.
Add sugar and honey; beat until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in milk.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture.
Beat well.
Fold in dates, cherries and nuts.
Drop dough from a teaspoon 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Top each with a pecan half or candied cherry, if desired.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
Makes 48.

title: blondies
directions: Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar to shortening.
Mix well.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture gradually, mixing well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix together soups, milk and mushrooms.
Set aside 1/2 cup of soup mixture.
Mix rice and thawed vegetables with remaining soup mixture and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice.
Pour remaining soup over the chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with assorted vegetable dippers or potato chips.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine the topping until crumbly. Sprinkle over the potatoes.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
(I have used different nuts and sometimes put some topping on the bottom of the pan since I love the coconut and nuts.)

title: oven baked chicken supreme
directions: Prepare four individual bowls with the following:
(1) melted butter, (2) flour and seasoning salt, (3) eggs and water, (4) bread crumbs and cheese.
Dip chicken in each bowl.
Fit a rack in 13 x 9-inch shallow baking dish.
"Pam" and put breasts on rack and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Put under broiler for a few minutes to brown.

title: 3 chocolate clusters
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients over low.
Stir in next 2 ingredients and drop onto greased paper.

title: guest chicken
directions: Place cleaned chicken breasts in 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Place 1 slice Swiss cheese on each.
Mix soup together and add milk to get a thinner consistency.
Pour over chicken.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks with milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Cook in double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove and let cool.
Add butter and vanilla.
Top with your favorite meringue recipe.

title: 2 layer raspberry salad or dessert
directions: Mix lemon jello and water; drain pineapple and heat juice to boil.
Add marshmallows; stir until dissolved.
Cool and add to lemon jello.
Mix softened cream cheese until smooth; add crushed pineapple.
Add to lemon mixture.
Whip the cream and fold into lemon mixture.
Put in large glass oblong pan and refrigerate. Dissolve raspberry jello and water.
Add 2 packages of almost thawed raspberries and carefully pour or spoon over lemon jello mixture and return to refrigerator.
Enjoy!

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Butter 2-quart baking dish.
Cover the bottom with 1/3 of plain saltines.
Add a layer of half the oysters, and season with salt, pepper and 1/8 teaspoon nutmeg.
Add 1/4 cup oyster liquor and 1/3 cup cream.
Add another 1/3 of the cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Add the remaining oysters, the seasonings and finally the remaining plain cracker crumbs.
Top with the buttered crushed saltines, the remaining 1/4 cup oyster liquor and 1/3 cup heavy cream.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dash Tabasco over all.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown on top.

title: squash balls (zucchini)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon into 1-inch deep hot oil; fry until golden brown.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, jello, sugar and boiling water until dissolved. Add cold water and mix.
Pour into molds and freeze.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar and add beaten eggs, vanilla and vinegar.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in nuts, raisins and coconut. Pour into an 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: beef or turkey jerky
directions: Slice meat thin, while frozen, or have it sliced at deli. Soak in solution of remaining ingredients for 24 hours; then bake at low temperature (275° to 300°) for 24 hours or place in dehydrator.

title: alabama chocolate pecan jumbo fudge pie
directions: Combine chocolate wafer crumbs and 1/3 c. melted butter, mixing well. Press into bottom and up sides of ungreased 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 6-8 minutes.

title: homemade applesauce
directions: Wash and quarter apples, cutting out the cores. (The more applesauce you want the more apples you need.)
Place apples (still in skins) in large pot with a little bit of water to add moisture.
Cook over medium heat with lid on, until apples are soft and mushy.
(Do not scorch.
You may have to lower the heat.)

title: oven stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a casserole; do not brown meat.
Stir all ingredients thoroughly.
Cover; bake at 250° for 4 hours.
Do not lift cover until done.
Serves 4.
Double recipe serves 6 to 7.

title: happy time cake
directions: Mix well cake mix, egg and margarine.
Pat down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla. Pour over cake mixture.
Top with chopped pecans.
Cook at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake pie crust in dish as directed.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour into crust.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate walnut wheels
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually. Add egg, melted baking chocolate and vanilla. Add flour, salt and nuts.
Beat well. Drop from tip of spoon 1-inch apart onto greased baking sheet. Garnish each with walnut halve. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen wheels.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Fry bacon until it just begins to brown and transfer into large casserole dish.
Season flour with salt and pepper to taste.
Place the pork chops in a bag with seasoned flour and shake to coat. Brown pork chops in the bacon fat.
Drain on paper towel.
Add brown sugar and garlic to skillet; cook, stirring for about 3 minutes.
Add the sauerkraut, berries and peppercorns.
Heat thoroughly.
Transfer it to the casserole dish and mix with the bacon.
Lay the pork chops on top.
Pour the beer and chicken stock over the pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until very tender.
Serves 6.

title: aunt pina's chili
directions: Place the olive oil in a saucepan and brown the ground beef. Place chopped onion, crushed red pepper, garlic powder and salt in the pan.
Place a lid on the pan and allow it to simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour in the can of sauce, water, parsley, basil and kidney beans and allow to simmer for another 15 minutes.
Enjoy the chili on top of a bowl of rice and a loaf of Italian bread.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Put into a buttered baking dish.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Crumble crackers on top of the cheese.
(Make sure your crackers are finely crumbled.)
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over the top of crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes until it has a brown crust on top.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Melt butter in a large saucepan; add onions and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until transparent. Add potatoes, bouillon and seasoning to onions.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Put mixture, half at a time, in blender and blend until smooth.
Transfer to pan and continue with rest of mixture. Add milk and heat thoroughly.
Garnish with parsley.

title: grandma's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes in hot oven (425°).
Reduce heat and bake 45 minutes in slow oven (350°).

title: dove pot pie
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Roll the dove breast in mixture, brown in oil and drain, then cover with water.
Add vegetables and simmer for 30 minutes.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with biscuits. Spread with butter.
Place in preheated oven at 400°.
Bake until biscuits are brown.

title: chocolate mocha drink mix
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Store in an airtight container.
To use, place 2 rounded teaspoonfuls in a cup of boiling water.
Makes a nice Christmas gift.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a boil milk and sugar for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into buttered dish.
Refrigerate until hard.

title: easy gumbo
directions: Saute vegetables and seasonings in oil until soft.
Add broth, water and brown gravy mix.
Cook one hour on simmer.
Add meat; heat thoroughly.
Serve over cooked rice.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: corn cheese soup
directions: Melt butter and lightly brown onion and baco chips.
Add corn and heat.
Add milk and potatoes.
Add seasonings and cheese. Heat until cheese is stringy.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.
Serve with Buttermilk Biscuits.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together hamburger, soup mix, egg, 1/2 of tomato sauce and bread (oatmeal).
When using bread, tear into small pieces.
Form into pan, 9 x 9-inch or loaf pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese with fork until smooth. Stir in crushed pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape into ball.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until well chilled, overnight.
May garnish with pineapple slices and cherries.
May be frozen.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce in bottom of trifle bowl.
In order and in layers, add cucumbers, celery, peppers, onions and peas.
Do not toss; leave in layers.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over layers of peas.
Sprinkle with sugar and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Sprinkle bacon over salad dressing before serving. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
With a spoon, blend in flour.
Add nuts; shape into 3/4-inch balls, rolling in palm of hand.
Place 1/2-inch apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake in preheated 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until cookies are creamy color.
Remove to rack until just warm.
Roll in a little confectioners sugar.
Cool entirely and roll again in confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen. Store in tightly covered container.

title: applesauce cake or cupcakes
directions: Cream together at slow speed 1 cup sugar, 1 egg, 1 cup applesauce, 1/2 cup shortening.
Add at medium speed 1 3/4 cup self-rising flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon cloves.
Stir into batter 1 cup chopped nuts and 1 cup raisins.
Bake cake 30 minutes at 350°.
Bake cupcakes 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients, stirring constantly until a soft ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Add 1/3 cup butter and let cool.
When candy is lukewarm, beat and stir in pecans.
Continue to stir until candy will hold its shape when dropped from teaspoon on waxed paper.
Makes 36 patties.

title: creamy chicken primavera
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter or margarine.
Add chicken. Cook until no longer pink.
Add pasta, vegetables and water. Cover and cook over medium heat 7 to 9 minutes until veggies are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mostaccioli (pasta) al fredo
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
In large pan, heat butter and cream on low heat.
Do not boil.
Add pasta, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Toss gently to coat.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: party peas
directions: Pour peas into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add milk; cover with cheese.
Broil under moderate heat until very lightly browned.
Garnish with paprika.
Serve hot. Makes 8 servings.

title: south of the border breakfast
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Make 4 indentations in mixture. Break eggs (one for each indentation).
Cover and cook 5 minutes. Sprinkle 8 ounces of Cheddar cheese over all; cook 1 minute, covered.
Serve with hot biscuits and jelly.
Recipe can be halved for 2 servings.

title: slumgullian(meal in a dish - texas style)
directions: Cook macaroni; do not overcook.
Heat oil in skillet.
Saute onion and green pepper until limp; do not brown.
Remove from skillet (use small bowl).
Place hamburg in skillet and simmer just until meat turns color.
Break up chunks and turn frequently. Add sauteed vegetables, tomatoes, salt and chili powder.
Simmer to blend all ingredients.

title: baked beans for 50 people
directions: Cook beans in soda water for 5 minutes. Drain and continue as for baked beans until done.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine sugar, milk and soda.
Cook until forms ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter and nuts.
Beat until creamy and will hold shape.
Drop on buttered paper.

title: cream pie recipe
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk, beaten egg yolks and butter.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.

title: lower fat turkey loaf
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together all ingredients until well blended.
Lightly brush bottom of loaf or baking pan with olive oil.
Spread and pat meat loaf mixture in pan; form a rounded loaf at top.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: sour cream rhubarb pie
directions: Place rhubarb in unbaked pie shell. Beat egg slightly. Add sour cream, sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Pour over rhubarb. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325°.
Continue baking for about 40 minutes until knife inserted midway between edge and center of pie comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: speedie rolls
directions: Combine water, yeast and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add salt and 2 cups of flour.
Beat for 2 minutes; add eggs and shortening.
Beat for 1 minute.
Blend in rest of flour.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 20 minutes, then roll out and make rolls.
Let rise again, then bake in 325° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: deviled dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together cottage cheese, ham, parsley, onion and pepper.
Cover and chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: orange pecans
directions: Boil to 230° or spins a thread.
Stir until begins to sugar. Add the pecans and pour into buttered pans.
Break apart when thoroughly cold and hardened.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter.
Remove from heat and add nuts and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and chill well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then wet ingredients together.
Makes 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2) loaf pans.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: coffman casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except hard-boiled eggs.
Put half of mixture in well buttered large casserole.
Sprinkle hard-boiled eggs on top.
Add other half of mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator; sprinkle crumbs if you like over top and bake 1 hour at 350°. Remove from oven and let set 10 minutes before serving.
Serves about 8 people.

title: russian cream
directions: Warm in double boiler.
Sprinkle gelatin into cup of water. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add to cream mixture.
Heat until gelatin dissolves.
Place pot in refrigerator until thickened slightly (2 hours or more).
Add vanilla to sour cream and add to cooked mixture.
Pour into dessert glasses.
Top with thawed raspberries and juice.

title: basque bean soup
directions: Rinse beans and put in crock-pot.
Cover with ample water, allowing for beans to expand and leaving room for other ingredients.
Soak overnight.
Add onion, chorizos, ham hock, oil, tomato sauce, bouillon, paprika, salt and garlic.
Slow cook all day.
Stir occasionally; add water, depending on desired consistency.
Ready to eat the next day.

title: auntie el's hamburg rice casserole
directions: Cook onion and hamburg; add carrots.
Mix 2 cups water and gravy before adding to mix.
Combine hamburg mix and rice.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put on cheese and bake 10 more minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Add sugar and fold in saltines and nuts.
Put in greased 7-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown; cool.
Then put on cherry pie filling and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and stir all remaining ingredients together.
Place in a bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You may add 1 cup of nuts (optional).

title: sunday pancakes
directions: Combine flour and milk.
Add melted butter or margarine, beat in eggs and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in very hot skillet. Serve with apricot or blackberry jam.
Top with whipped cream.

title: shaker lemon pie
directions: Slice the lemons, rind and all, tissue paper thin. Add sugar and let stand overnight.
Beat the eggs until creamy smooth and light color. Add to sugar and lemon mixture.
Combine well.
Pour into pie shell. Cover with pricked top pie crust.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes and 45 minutes at 400°.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and 1/2 cup powdered sugar in a large bowl.
Stir in vanilla and almond extract.
Mix in flour, pecans and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Chill until firm, 1 hour.

title: chicken baked in sour cream
directions: Dredge chicken in flour and salt and pepper.
Put in casserole or baking dish.
Pour sour cream, soup and mushrooms over.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 375° to 400°.

title: guacamole dip
directions: In a medium size bowl, mash avocados.
Mix sour cream, garlic powder, salt, lemon or lime juice, green chiles and Tabasco sauce. Stir in onion and tomato; mix well.
May be refrigerated up to 2 days.

title: waffles
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together, then beat in the rest of ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold this in batter until smooth.
Bake in hot waffle iron.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
In saucepan, melt butter and blend in flour.
Stir in milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat and fold in cheese.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine cooked macaroni with cheese sauce.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a small saucepan; stir in the water.
Cook until clear and thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until the butter is melted.
Serve hot.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place ground beef in a 9 x 15-inch baking dish.
Slice onion thin and press into top of meat.
Add Tater Tots on top of meat and onion.

title: sandies
directions: Make dough and form into egg shaped rolls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 275° for 45 to 60 minutes. When done, roll in powdered sugar. Use extra sugar for rolling if needed.

title: strawberry ice cream (cooked)(makes 4 quarts)
directions: Scald milk and stir thoroughly and slowly into well beaten eggs, 1 cup of sugar, salt and flour.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from fire and when cold, fold in cream, whipped stiff.
When partially frozen, stir in, thoroughly, the strawberries which have been crushed and pressed through a sieve and sweetened with remaining sugar. Freeze.

title: mexican corn
directions: Combine corn, chilies, onion and cream cheese.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare muffin mix by directions on box.
Bake and crumble in bowl when cool.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowls. Pour over crumbled bread.
Chill.
Best if prepared the day before you serve.

title: blender cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender for 7 minutes and pour into 9 or 10-inch pie dish or quiche pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve chilled with berries or chocolate sauce. Excellent!
Can use light cream cheese if desired.

title: firehouse chili
directions: Mix Chianti, water, chili powder, salt, oregano, cumin, fennel seed, sage, mint leaves, steak sauce and chocolate syrup; mix well.
Brown meat, onions and garlic.
Drain fat and add peppers, juice from kidney beans, tomatoes, pepperoni, shallots and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Stir in kidney beans and simmer for another 15 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix and melt marshmallow and milk in a double boiler over low heat.
In graham cracker crumbs (rolled fine), put cherries, nuts and raisins in large bowl and mix well.
Pour milk and marshmallows over crumbs.
Mix real good.
Pack back in the cracker box and put in the refrigerator for a week.
Can also be packed in a loaf pan.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Steam broccoli for 5 minutes.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Combine mushroom mixture, broccoli and water chestnuts.
Set aside.
Combine processed cheese and soup; cook over low heat, stirring until cheese melts.
Pour over broccoli mixture; stir in garlic salt and pepper.
Bake in a greased 2-quart casserole, covered, for 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: idiot beans
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and dump into crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions; drain and dump into crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 6 hours.

title: world's easiest dump cake
directions: Melt margarine in square Pyrex-type pan.
Mix together sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Pour into melted margarine. Do not stir.
Sprinkle any fresh fruit on top.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cherry or blueberry tart pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, brown sugar and melted butter.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Spread cracker crumb mixture in 9-inch baking pan, then pour other mixture in this pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool and add can of cherry or blueberry pie mix. Let cool in refrigerator and top with Cool Whip.

title: jelly cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add all other ingredients.
Form small balls.
Press thumb in center of each ball and fill with jelly or candied fruit.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions on package and add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and let set until firm in refrigerator.
Cook sugar, egg, flour and pineapple juice until thick.
Add margarine and cool.
Add topping to Cool Whip.
Spread over Jell-O mix and let set.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix well and pour in container.

title: power shake
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender at high speed until thick and foamy, about 30 seconds.
Pour into glasses.
If desired, other fruits may be substituted for strawberries.
Makes 2 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Grease large roasting pan.
Pour popped corn and peanuts in pan.
In saucepan on top of stove, melt margarine.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Bake 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Break apart.
Store covered.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Combine the brown sugar and pecans; set aside.
Combine all other ingredients and beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour 1/3 batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of brown sugar mixture. Pour remaining batter on this and sprinkle with remaining brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: all day pie
directions: Take labels off the sweetened condensed milk and place unopened in a Dutch oven (a big pot with a lid).

Fill almost full with water and boil cans slowly for 3 hours, uncovered. As the water evaporates, keep adding more hot water so the cans remain covered the entire time. After 3 hours, carefully remove from water and put them in the refrigerator to cool. Open cans and slide out of can. Set aside.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
In large bowl, combine hamburger with lettuce, beans, cheese, onion, tomatoes and avocado.
Cool. Just before serving add chips and dressing.
Toss well.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: With a blender or fork, mix first 4 ingredients.
In separate dish, beat remaining ingredients.
Combine the 2 mixtures, stirring with a fork until all is moistened.
With hands, mold dough into a ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling. Dough can be left in refrigerator for 3 days, or frozen until ready to use.
Makes about 4 (9-inch) crusts.

title: baked halibut steaks
directions: Lightly grease a medium baking dish. Heat olive oil in medium saucepan over medium heat, and stir in zucchini, onion, and garlic. Cook and stir 5 minutes or until tender. Remove saucepan from heat, mix in tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.

title: refrigerator  rolls
directions: Put yeast in bowl with warm water, and stir until dissolved. Add shortening, sugar, eggs,
6 c. of the flour and salt.
Stir and beat until smooth, about 1 minute. Add the
remaining 2 - 2 1/2 c. flour, and kneed. This makes a soft dough.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator overnight, or up to 2 - 3 days.
Punch down and pinch off, however much is needed.
Make walnut size balls, and place onto greased cookie sheet.
Let double in size. Bake at 375 degrees for 12 - 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: water and oil crust(delicious and easy)
directions: Place flour, oil, salt and water in a bowl and mix quickly. Do not overwork the dough or it will become tough.
Divide into two portions.
Put wax paper or plastic wrap on counter or large cutting board and place one portion of dough on it.

Gently pat out the round of dough until it is about six inches in diameter. Place the other piece of wrap on top of the dough and roll out until the dough is the size of the pie dish with an extra 1-inch all around.
Remove the top wrap and flip the dough over into the pie dish and then peel the bottom wrap off.
Repeat the procedure for the top crust, except wait until the filling is in the pie dish before placing the top crust in place.
Makes top and bottom crust.
For two crusts, double the ingredients.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Place meat in heavy kettle. cover with hot water.
Cover tightly and simmer about 3 hr. skim off excess fat and add onions, carrots, potatoes and turnips. Cover and cook 20 min. Add cabbage and continue cooking 10 to 15 minutes. 8 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Melt shortening.
Add applesauce, sugar, cinnamon, allspice, cloves, and salt.
Heat thoroughly.
Add flour and soda.
Stir in egg.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: fried ripe tomatoes with gravy
directions: Cut
tomatoes into 1/3-inch slices and dredge in flour. Set aside 1 tablespoon remaining flour.

title: endless coleslaw
