directions: In large bowl combine cabbage, peppers and onion; set aside. To make dressing:
In saucepan combine vinegar, oil, sugar, dry mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour hot dressing over cabbage mixture and toss well.
Let stand at room temperature for 60 minutes, tossing occasionally.
For best flavor, cover and refrigerate two days before serving.
Keeps refrigerated up to 10 days.

title: slush punch
directions: I use a dishpan to mix all the ingredients.
Add boiling water to gelatin and stir to dissolve. Add cold water and stir.
Add pineapple juice and sugar; stir.
Put in freezer Baggies and freeze.
You can make this punch up a week before you need it. Take out of freezer about 5 to 6 hours before serving. Add ginger ale to your taste.

title: easter cookies(koulourakia pashalina)
directions: Sift 11 cups of flour with the baking powder into a glass bowl; scoop out a well in it.
Brown the butter and pour into the flour.
Let stand until cool enough to handle.

title: polynesian wedding cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with hand mixer.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix together, using a wooden spoon.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix with biscuit mix and sausage.
Shape into balls and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Freeze if desired after baking, then heat in oven for a few minutes when ready to serve.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook until thick; add sugar to taste.
Mushrooms can be added if desired.
Put into cans and cold pack for 1/2 hour.

title: watsons' egg vantage
directions: Very lightly butter an 8-inch pie pan.
Place drained peppers (cut up) in pan.
Next, sprinkle with cheeses and ther rest.
Pour beaten eggs over this and sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: baked fish
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Spray flat pan with Pam.
Put fillets skin side down.
Spray lightly with Pam.
Cover fillets with dry mixture.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Low calorie, low-fat and very good.

title: fresh strawberry soup
directions: Puree all ingredients in blender.
Refrigerate covered at least 6 hours or overnight.
Serve chilled.
Garnish with mint leaves.

title: whiskey sour slush
directions: Mix well and freeze in a plastic juice pitcher.
To serve, add a maraschino cherry and an orange slice.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Ways and one stick of margarine and set aside to cool.
Cream sugar and two remaining sticks of margarine; add beaten eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add buttermilk, soda, flour and vanilla.
Mix well with candy and margarine mixture and add nuts (optional).
Bake at 325° until done.
You can use the fudge recipe on the back of the Marshmallow Creme jar, but this one is not as rich.

title: mandarin jello delight
directions: Mix 2 packages lemon Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water; mix well.
Use the reserved juice and add water to make 1 cup; add to Jell-O and stir well.
Put Jell-O into refrigerator to cool for about one hour.
Beat Dream Whip per instructions on package; stir in Jell-O and fruit until mixed.
Set to mold.
Spread 1 cup sour cream over top before serving.

title: irish salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling point; do not boil.
Add jello and marshmallows; stir lightly until dissolved.
Remove from heat. When slightly cooled, add cottage cheese and nuts.
Pour into 6 x 10-inch Pyrex dish.
Place in refrigerator.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate.

title: ruth's sausage and potatoes
directions: Cut sausage into bite size pieces.
Place in a large skillet; add water just to cover sausage.
Let simmer until all water is cooked out, then brown and drain grease.
Add Ro-Tel and 1 cup of water.
Add all other ingredients; let cook until potatoes are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: good old fashion potato salad fat-free
directions: Boil eggs, peeled and cut into half, discarding the yolk.
(I always mix the yolk in with my dog's food.
They love it.)
Peel and chunk up potatoes.
Add the egg whites, onion, pickles and mix. Add mustard and mix.
Last but not least, add the fat-free mayo. Mix. There you have it.
Old fashion potatoes minus the fat. Yields 5 servings.
Has 80 calories, fat freee!!!!
Enjoy.

title: heath bar bake
directions: Bake cake according to box.
While still warm, poke holes with wooden spoon and pour milk.
Cool cake in fridge.
Pour on caramel, then Cool Whip, then Heath bars.

title: quick pig in a blanket
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper.

title: banana pudding
directions: Pour milk into saucepan over medium heat and let it get hot. Mix sugar and flour together in a bowl.
When milk is hot, pour beaten egg in, then add dry mixture (sugar and flour).
Stir and remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Layer bananas, cookies and pudding.

title: lasagna
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Brown Italian sausage, ground chuck, onion and garlic; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and spices.

title: yogurt dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl. Cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving. Serve with fresh vegetables. Yield: 8 servings.

title: cheesy mixed vegetable bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a large casserole dish. Combine vegetables, half of the pimiento, soup, sour cream, pepper, half of the fried onions and half of the cheese in a bowl; mix. Spoon mixture into prepared casserole dish. Bake for 20 minutes. Sprinkle remaining fried onions and cheese on top of casserole. Bake casserole for 5 minutes longer. Remove casserole from oven. Sprinkle with remaining pimiento. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut pocket in each chop along fat side.
Salt and pepper inside of pocket.
Toss together bread cubes, apple, cheese and raisins.
Combine melted butter, orange juice, salt and cinnamon. Pour over bread mixture and mix gently.
Stuff into pork chops lightly.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Cover with foil; bake 15 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot seafood salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in a buttered casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven.
Crumble corn flakes on top and bake for 20 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cobbler
directions: Pour fruit cocktail in a mixing bowl.
Add 2/3 box of cake mix.
Mix well.
Melt oleo and add to batter.
Pour in a medium size Pyrex bowl and bake at 325°.
Test with toothpicks to make sure inside is done.
The cobbler will brown lightly on top. Serve warm with whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook the egg noodles in the broth left from the chicken; drain. Reserve 1 cup of broth for the casserole. Mix the Velveeta cheese, soup and the chicken. Top with the shredded Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbling around edges.

title: yummy custard pie
directions: Blend eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle just a tiny bit of nutmeg on top (not much, as it will get too brown).
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: cherry o cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Whip while adding Eagle Brand until smooth. Add lemon and vanilla.
Blend well. Pour into crust.
Chill several hours.
Top with cherries.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Fry sausage and drain; put in pie shell.
Beat eggs, salt and pepper; pour over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: frank's mother-in-law's pumpkin bread
directions: *If you use mini chocolate chips, use 2 cups of sugar and 1 cup of chips.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well, store in jar or can for future use. Use 1-2 tsp. per cup hot water.

title: cornbread corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 400° for 1 hour without lid.
Great for reunions and potlucks.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water for 7 minutes or until they can be pierced with a fork.
Pour off almost all water.
Add brown sugar, several dashes of cloves and nutmeg and butter.
Stir to coat carrots.
Simmer for 3 minutes on medium to low heat.

title: baked carrots
directions: Wash and peel carrots; cut lengthways.
Have 2 pieces of foil going in both ways.
Place carrots and remaining ingredients on first foil sheet; wrap loosely on top of other foil.
Also wrap (no seams).
Put in oven with whatever is baking for 1 hour or more.
Cannot overcook.

title: family favorite creamed corn
directions: Slice cream cheese and margarine.
Combine with remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook at low setting for 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
To double recipe, defrost corn slightly and cook on high for 4 hours.

title: lime applesauce jello
directions: Heat applesauce. Add dry jello and dissolve.
Add 7-Up and chill.

title: rouladen
directions: Lay slices of beef on table; lay on slice of bacon, chopped onion, salt, pepper and thin slice of pickle (optional).
Roll up and stick with toothpick so they do not unroll.
Sear rouladen in oil until browned.
Cover with heated water in heavy pot or Dutch oven, add bouillon cubes.
Simmer until tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours. thicken gravy in manner you desire, (cornstarch, roux or flour and water).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: great grandma's gingerbread(100 years old)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg, molasses and all dry ingredients.
Add hot water last, beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: marie's chicken salad
directions: Chop vegetables and eggs.
Add Beau Monde, pepper and garlic powder to Miracle Whip which has been thoroughly mixed with cream cheese.
Combine chopped vegetables, eggs, chicken and Miracle Whip mixture.
Serve on lettuce and tomato plate.

title: cashew nut chops
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk with dissolved broth.
Add cracker crumbs and ground nuts.
Spread in a greased 6 x 10-inch baking pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into glass dish.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: apple knobble cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Mix apples.
Sift together flour, soda and spices.
Blend into batter.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Serve warm with whipped cream or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in skillet in oil.
Place rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Arrange chops on top of rice.
Place bell pepper rings, tomatoes and onion slices on top of each chop.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour tomato juice over all.
Sprinkle with basil.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: In a heavy pot combine broth, water, lentils, tomatoes, carrots, onion, celery, garlic, basil, oregano, thyme and bay leaf.
Bring to boil and simmer covered for two hours.
Stir in parsley, vinegar and salt and pepper to taste.
Discard bay leaf. Thin soup, if desired, with water or chicken broth.

title: brown mushroom sauce for fondue
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour; remove from heat. Stir in consomme soup.
Return to heat; cook until thickened.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: coffee-orange fudge cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch fluted tube pan.
In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, sour cream, oil, water, eggs and pudding mix.
Dissolve instant coffee in 1/4 cup water.
Mix with other ingredients along with orange peel and cinnamon.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed until blended, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: tortellini
directions: Brown hamburger; pour off excess grease. Salt to taste.

Melt butter; add basil, cornstarch and cream to make medium sauce. Place meat in bottom of pan or baking dish. Cover with tortellini, then sauce and lastly with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cover 10 minutes, then remove for 15 minutes until brown.

title: kraut and frank stew
directions: Brown wieners in oil; remove and set aside.
Add onion to oil; saute until lightly brown.
Add tomatoes that are chopped; cook. Cook carrots and potatoes in water until part way done.
Then add tomatoes, onions, pepper and kraut.
Boil until done.
Add wieners and boil 5 minutes.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add 2 eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add molasses and water or milk and mix well.
Add spices and soda to the flour; mix well.
Add to the other mixture, then add the fruit.
The dough will be quite stiff.
Form into rolls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on the width of the cookie sheet. Press flat, coat with the white of egg which has been slightly beaten.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Test with toothpick. Cut into bars while warm.
Makes approximately
36 bars.

title: chicken a la reuben(low cholesterol)
directions: Place uncooked chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, sprayed with Pam.
Pour bottle of Thousand Island dressing over chicken breast, then dump can of
sauerkraut, juice and all, over the dressing.
Top with sliced Swiss cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rye rolls or bread.

title: spectacular brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 1/4 cup butter together and cool.
Cream sugar and 2 eggs; add to cooled chocolate.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; add to chocolate mixture.
Butter and flour 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour 1/2 of chocolate mixture in pan.
Then continue with cream cheese and butter mixed together.
Mix egg, vanilla and sugar in separate bowl.
Add to cream cheese mixture along with 1 tablespoon flour.

title: cranbanana berry cooler
directions: Combine water and sugar.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients, except ginger ale. Freeze for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove from the freezer about 30 minutes before serving.
Transfer to a wide mouth pitcher and add ginger ale.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water.
When soft, rub through a strainer.
There should be 2 1/2 cups of scalded milk with onion. Remove the onion and slowly whisk milk into the potatoes.
Melt half of the butter and add the flour, salt, celery salt, pepper and cayenne.
Stir well mixed, then stir into the hot soup.
Boil for 1 minute.
Strain and add the remaining butter.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: beef roast
directions: Put salt and pepper on roast; dust with flour and brown in 3 tablespoons oil.
Take out and put in a big roast pan.
Put potatoes, cut in quarters around roast.
Add carrots cut in about 1-inch pieces.
In pan where meat was browned, add 3 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper and brown.
Add enough water to make a thin gravy.
Add chopped onions and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over roast and potatoes and carrots.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for about 3 hours.

title: lima bean salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together lightly.
Chill for at least one hour before serving.
Chopped lettuce may also be used.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, then water.
Beat well.
Use about 1 inch of 1 stick of butter to grease pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cholesterol split pea soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pan.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
If too thick, add a little more water and stir. Serve immediately or freeze.
Add a few potatoes if desired. Serves 6.

title: hard top cake
directions: Blend sugar and Crisco.
Add 1 egg at a time, mixing well each time.
Add flour and vanilla and/or nutmeg.
Spray Bundt pan; pour in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Forms crust on top.
Take up immediately.
Can leave upside down or flip over.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Great plain or served with strawberries.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in crust.
Add fruit on top (optional).

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan or dish and spread the pineapple and juice over the bottom of the pan.
Add a layer of berries and the 3/4 cup sugar.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of fruit layer, then drizzle melted butter over dry cake mix.
Top with nuts.
Finally for a crunch, add the remaining 1/4 cup sugar. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Take a spoon and cut down into cake so juices will come up.

title: chiles rellenos
directions: Broil bell peppers, peel skin off. Cut bell peppers in the middle, remove seeds. Brown ground beef, drain.
Add Jack cheese and cook until done.
Beat eggs, add flour and salt.
Fill bell peppers with ground beef mixture.
Dip bell peppers into egg mixture and fry until done.
Dip cooked bell peppers into tomato sauce.
Continue cooking for 10 to 15 minutes more.
Serve with rice.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, shortenings, yolk of egg and milk. Divide in half. Roll out size of cookie sheet. Sprinkle Krispies on unbaked crust. Add sliced apples, sugar and cinnamon. Put top crust on top. Beat egg white and spread on crust. Bake 40 minutes at 400°. While hot, dribble on powdered sugar frosting.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Combine bacon, onion, broccoli and raisins. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over marinade 1/2 to 1 hour before serving.

title: raisin walnut cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water in a small saucepan; bring to a boil. Cook for 3 minutes. Remove from heat; let cool (do not drain). In a mixing bowl, cream shortening; gradually add sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients in separate bowl; add to creamed mixture and blend thoroughly. Stir in nuts and raisins. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes. Do not overbake. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine in large 6-quart pan chopped butter, sugar and milk. Bring to a boil and cook 6 minutes on medium heat or 235° on candy thermometer.
Add chocolate chips, chopped Hershey bar and marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Add nuts.
Put in two large 9 x 13-inch pans or 1 larger pan.
Pans should be greased.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: pumpkin pie(serves 8; 0 grams of cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake pie crust until lightly browned. Remove from oven and let cool to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bowl, beat all filling ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 50 minutes more or until knife in center of pie is clean.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, peanut butter, eggs and vanilla; then add dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls and press lightly with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.
I have quadrupled this recipe with the same good results.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening until well mixed.
Add milk and stir until soft dough is formed.
Knead dough on lightly floured board and shape into smooth ball.
Roll into 1/2-inch thick lengths and cut with floured biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake in very hot oven at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 14 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender. Drain and keep hot.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Stir in just enough mayonnaise to hold other ingredients together.
Use the woody stems of broccoli; peel and chop.
They have a nutty flavor and rich in nutrients.

title: eight layer salad
directions: Line large Pyrex dish with spinach.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese, bacon, onion, lettuce, peas and eggs.
Mix cream and mayonnaise.
Add 1/4 cup cheese.
Spread on top of salt; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Chill 24 hours.

title: spinach salad
directions: In blender, mix sugar, cider vinegar, dry mustard and salt. Once blended, add 1/2 cup minced red onion and oil.
Blend well. Let stand 2 hours.
To serve, toss spinach, remaining red onion, bacon bits, egg and shredded carrots with dressing on top.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place the bread cubes in a 9 x 12-inch greased baking dish, sprinkling the raisins throughout.
Beat together the rest of the ingredients and pour over the bread.
Allow to soak overnight, refrigerated.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Use meat from boiling meat.
Boil meat until done, then cut up.
Cook each vegetable separately and add to pot.
Add bouillon cubes and simmer at least 1/2 hour.

title: walt's famous chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Mix your favorite pancake mix and prepare to put on griddle. After spooning mix onto griddle, place small chocolate chips on top of soon-to-be pancake.
Immediately spoon a small amount of mix on top to cover chips.
Turn once to brown on both sides. Serve as you would normal pancakes, but with less butter and possibly less syrup, depending on your sweet tooth.

title: nutmeg log cookies
directions: Cream margarine or butter with vanilla, rum flavoring and sugar.
Add egg, flour and nutmeg.
On floured surface, roll dough into thin log and cut into 3-inch pieces.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup crumbs on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan coated with cooking spray.
Set remaining 1/4 cup crumbs aside. Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add cream cheese and next 5 ingredients.
Process until smooth.
Add egg substitute and process just until blended.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes or until center is almost set.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup remaining crumbs.
Let cool completely on wire rack. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Top each slice with small amount of reduced whipped cream and sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Yields 16 servings (226 calories, 2.1 g fat).

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup until bubbly.
Mix gelatin envelope with cold water until dissolved; then add to soup.
Simmer for a few minutes and then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a mold and chill at least 8 hours.
Serve with Ritz crackers or whatever.

title: no cholesterol egg substitute
directions: Separate
eggs.
Beat
egg whites slightly.
Add nonfat dry milk.
Beat.
Let
rest
until nonfat dry milk dissolves. Add 3 to 4 drops of yellow food coloring.
Mix equals 3 eggs. You can freeze mixture for future use.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, onion and celery. Mix together Ranch dressing mix, mayo and water. Pour over potatoes, onion and celery. Toss gently to coat. Refrigerate until well chilled, 1 to 2 hours.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Add all vegetables, dressing and seasoning to spaghetti. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sin dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Hollow out the bread.
Save the top.
Put ingredients in bread and put the top back on.
Cover in 2 to 3 layers of aluminum foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In large skillet, brown beef, onions and celery.
Drain off fat; add remaining ingredients (except cheese).
Cook 10 minutes, then add cheese.
Cook until melted.
Serve on buns.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Serves 50.

title: roast beef and mushroom gravy
directions: In large roasting pan combine beef, carrots, onion, mushrooms and soup.
Cook at 350° until beef and carrots are tender, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Best served over egg noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: french pot roast
directions: Brown beef in Dutch oven.
Add consomme, tomato paste, vegetables and seasonings.
Cover and roast in slow oven (275°) for 5 to 6 hours until done.

title: grapefruit gelatin salad
directions: Dilute sugar in hot pineapple juice.
Dilute gelatine in water.
Mix all ingredients together, put into mold.
Makes about 20 to 24 servings.
(May want to spray mold with Pam first.)

title: salsa de carlos
directions: Put all in blender and barely blend.
Chill.

title: *fluffy marshmallow icing
directions: Boil sugar, water and cream of tartar until syrup spins.
Stir in marshmallows.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Pour hot syrup slowly over egg whites.
Beat well and add vanilla.

title: nut cookies(year 1917)
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, flour and nuts.
Add salt and vanilla.
Drop with teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and keep water.
Fry bacon. Add onion, celery and green pepper. Cook 5 minutes. Stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar, vinegar and water. Bring to a boil.
Pour over potatoes and mix.

title: easy rolls
directions: Let margarine soften and mix well with sour cream.
Add flour and mix well.
Spoon into ungreased muffin tins.
Cook at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen regular size or 2 dozen small size rolls.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Heat pressure cooker (high heat).
Add fat.
Saute onions until golden.
Stir in ham and rice.
Cook until rice is golden.
Add seasonings, water and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Add shrimp.
Sprinkle green pepper over top.
Cover and cook about 8 minutes after steam is up in cooker.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix ingredients; bring to a boil.

title: squash casserole
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add squash and saute for 5 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Combine all ingredients, except potato chips and mix well.
Pour over squash. Pour mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift the flour with the baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Beat the oil with the sugar and egg until creamed.
Fold the sifted flour into the creamed mixture, alternating with the grated apple and vanilla, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add the chopped nuts last.
Pour into a buttered 10-inch tube or Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool in the pan 10 minutes before turning onto a rack to cool completely.

title: fudge crispies
directions: In a saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Watch carefully and do not burn.
Combine flour, sugar and salt; add to chocolate mixture.
Remove from heat and stir well.
Stir in eggs, vanilla and, finally, nuts.
Spread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool in pan on a wire rack; cut into squares when cool.

title: baked potatoes with shrimp sauce
directions: Drain shrimp, reserving liquid; set shrimp aside.
Combine 1/4 cup of reserved liquid and butter in a saucepan and heat.
Stir in egg yolks and cream.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in salt, sour cream, ginger, chili sauce and parsley.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes. Stir in shrimp.
Split potatoes lengthwise on tops, then force open.
Spoon sauce over each potato.
Serves 4.

title: poor boy taco
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix in taco seasoning.
Add dash of salt and pepper. Boil grated carrots and potatoes in enough water to cover.
When tender, drain well and add to meat mixture.
Cook over low heat until well blended.
Spread desired amount of mixture on flour tortillas.
Add sour cream to taste.
Roll up.

title: broccoli-crab casserole
directions: Remove crust from the bread, then cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
In a large bowl combine bread cubes, milk and mayonnaise, stir well.
Cover and refrigerate about 30 minutes.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Whole cranberries will burst as they bake.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: prize winning burrito bake
directions: Mix Bisquick, water and beans.
Spread in greased pie plate. Layer remaining ingredients on bean mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Serve with chopped lettuce, chopped tomato and sour cream if desired.

title: pineapple banana cake
directions: Measure the dry ingredients and sift together.
Dice bananas and measure quantity.
Add bananas to the dry ingredients along with the oil.
Add eggs, vanilla, crushed pineapple and juice from the pineapple.
Stir to blend but do not beat.
Pour into greased 9-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Set aside to cool without removing from pan.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells using package directions.
Brown ground beef and onion in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Pour off drippings.
Stir in seasonings, mixing well.
Combine ground beef with eggs, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and 1/3 of the Mozzarella cheese, mixing well.
Stuff manicotti cheese with mixture.
Arrange in baking dish.
Top with any remaining ground beef mixture, spaghetti sauce and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir in blueberries.
Pour into 12 x 8-inch dish; chill until set.
In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla and sour cream; mix well.
Spread over gelatin layer; sprinkle with pecans.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
From "Taste of Home" magazine.

title: chocolate-dipped rice krispy pops(children's recipe)
directions: You will also need 24 wooden sticks.

title: apple cake pie
directions: Place apples in well-greased 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; cover with 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream together margarine and remaining 1/2 cup sugar; add egg and mix.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix with creamed mixture and spread over fruit.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve hot or cold, with thin custard sauce or whipped cream. Makes 8 servings.
Ice cream is very good with it too.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls and broil.
Mix with sauce.

title: oriental express
directions: Toss and serve with Oriental Dressing.

title: oven fried chicken(serves 6)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In plastic bag combine potato flakes and seasonings.
In shallow bowl, combine egg and lemon juice.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture; shake in plastic bag.
Place chicken skin-side up in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Bake uncovered at 375° for 60 to 75 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Saute onion and celery in butter until tender, then add to other ingredients. Pour into casserole and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown on top.

title: curry chicken
directions: Have chicken cooked.
Cook broccoli until almost tender. Place broccoli in 2-quart baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Mix cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, milk, cheese, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.

title: impossibly easy chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease 9 x 1 1/4 pie plate.

title: nut cream cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar, then add the egg yolks and grated rinds; beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Stir 2 tablespoons of this mixture into the nuts. Fold nuts, dry ingredients and sour cream into the egg yolk mixture.
Lastly, beat the egg whites until stiff and fold in lightly.
Butter and flour a spring-form cake pan.
Turn in the mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until the cake tests done. Remove from the oven.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove the spring sides of the pan.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: baked apple crunch
directions: Place apples in a baking dish.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Mix dry ingredients with margarine.
Mixture should be crumbly.
Pour this over apples.
Sprinkle with the cinnamon.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Topping will be golden light brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Fold in egg with ground meat.
Add bread crumbs and onion, mixing gently.
Stir in cream, seasonings and 2 tablespoons of the chili sauce.
Shape into loaf.
Spray a loaf pan with vegetable cooking spray and set loaf inside.
Press a shallow hole down the center of the loaf and spread the remaining chili sauce over the loaf.
Cook at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: chili by larry
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Add in onion and green pepper. Saute until tender. Add in rest of ingredients. Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Makes about 4 servings.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and milk and then fold in pineapple, margarine and bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in an uncovered, greased 2-quart casserole.
Serves 6.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions and divide batter into two equal parts.
Melt 1 stick of butter, put into 1/2 batter with 1/2 milk and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let set 10 minutes.
Melt caramels and 1 stick butter along with other 1/2 of milk, then pour over cake.
Add 1 cup pecans to remaining batter.
Pour over caramel layer and bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes.
Ready to eat now!
Good!!!

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms, remove stems.
Chop stems of mushrooms and combine with butter and onions.
Saute for about 5 minutes.
Add fresh bread crumbs, walnuts, salt and pepper.
Butter the cap of each mushroom.
Place in pan and fill.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin soup with dumplings
directions: Cook pumpkin in water to cover until tender.
Mash.
Add milk; bring to boil.
Beat eggs and
1/4 cup water.
Add flour mix.
Add by spoonful to hot pumpkin and cook at least 5 minutes.
Add sugar, salt and nutmeg to taste.

title: orange roughy
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic, saute 7 minutes or until tender.
Add bell pepper and tomatoes.
Cook over medium-high heat 3 minutes.
Add fish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Turn fish over.
Cover and simmer another 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Transfer fish to serving plate reserving cooking sauce in skillet. Spoon sauce over fish.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
When mixed and no lumps, add milk and cook until creamy (low heat).
Stir to prevent lumping.
Add salt if desired and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted and smooth. Pour over cooked vegetables; broccoli, cauliflower, etc.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until mixture begins to bubble.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Beat eggs slightly and soften shortening.
Sift all dry ingredients together and combine all the ingredients, stirring well until all are mixed.
Flour a board or hard surface and roll out dough.
Cut with cookie cutter and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese, garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Mix margarine and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits before removing from baking sheet.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees.
Mix eggs and cream cheese.
Add sugar and vanilla, mix until fluffy.
Place one vanilla wafer in each cupcake liner in a muffin pan.
Fill liners 3/4 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Top with 1 Tbsp of pie filling.
Chill.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Put meat in oven and reduce heat to 325° for 1 hour. Rub loin with soy sauce and then with Italian salad dressing. Should be medium-rare or check with meat thermometer.

title: nancy's low-fat venison chili
directions: Brown venison and hamburger meat in skillet until done.
Drain and put in large 3-quart or more saucepan.
Add tomato sauces and tomatoes, onion, sugar and garlic.
Follow directions on 2-alarm chili packages, then simmer chili for one hour before adding masa and chili beans.

After 1 hour add masa powder as per directions on chili mix, then add chili beans and simmer for 15 minutes longer. If you prefer a spicier chili, add cayenne pepper in chili mix. Serve with chopped onions and shredded Healthy Favorites Cheddar cheese, premium fat-free crackers or low-fat oyster crackers.
For a 3-way, boil spaghetti or macaroni and add to chili.

title: macaroni-tomato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Place cooked macaroni, cheese, salt and pepper in alternate layers in buttered 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch oblong baking dish.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients in a large bowl. Gently stir in frozen blackberries until sugar mixture is crumbly. Spoon fruit mixture into a lightly greased 11 x 17-inch baking dish. Cut pie crust into 1/2-inch wide strips and arrange strips diagonally over blackberry mixture. Sprinkle top with 1 tablespoon sugar. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown and is bubbly. Serve with vanilla ice cream. Prep: 10 minutes. Bake: 45 minutes.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend for 1 minute.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
No crust!
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
For plain custard pie, omit coconut.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake and pudding according to package directions. Cake is baked in 3 layer size pans.
Mix together fruit and pudding in a bowl before using.

title: pizza dip
directions: (The amount of ingredients depends on the size of your pizza pan.)

title: zippy deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yellow and put in bowl.
Mix the ingredients with the yellow well and put into egg white halves.

title: request punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine soup and sour cream.
Add squash, onion, water chestnuts, pimento, salt and pepper.
Mix margarine and dressing; add 1/2 to other ingredients and pour into greased baking dish. Top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Saute onion and chopped garlic.
Place raw rice into pan and stir until coated with oil.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Place in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover and add cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: cheddar-bacon spread
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium-low heat, cook bacon until browned.
Remove to paper towels to drain.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
In blender at medium speed or in food processor with knife blade attached, blend Cheddar cheese and remaining ingredients until smooth.
Stir in crumbled bacon.
If not serving right away, cover and refrigerate.
To serve, remove spread to room temperature to soften slightly.
Serve with crackers.

title: tea spiced prunes
directions: Place prunes, orange and lemon slices and cinnamon in a saucepan; add enough water to cover.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add tea and brew 5 minutes; remove tea bags and cinnamon.
Add sugar and stir carefully until sugar is dissolved. Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 6 servings at 188 calories per serving.

title: carbonera(serves 4)
directions: Cook pasta.
Melt butter.
Whisk eggs, add cheese, wine, garlic, bacon and butter (melted).
Mix with hot pasta (which cooks eggs).
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate cheese delight
directions: Mix together with fork and press into glass baking dish.
Bake at 300° until lightly brown, about 15 minutes.

title: apple dumb cake
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
In another bowl mix the next 3 ingredients together.
Combine together and mix adding nuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut stems from mushrooms; chop stems.
Saute large mushroom caps in butter and remove from pan.
Saute stems in remaining butter in pan.
Add bread crumbs, nuts, cheese and basil.
Mix well, heat thoroughly.
Fill mushroom caps.
Freeze until ready to use.
Heat thoroughly under broiler.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; add garlic powder, chili powder, salt and pepper; drain. Layer in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole as follows: Tortillas, meat, beans, onions and cheese. Top with tortillas. Pour soup and Ro-Tel tomato mixture over all. Cover with foil. Cook in 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and cook 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: baked steak
directions: Cut steak into serving-size pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread butter on meat.
Add mushrooms and sprinkle with soup.
Cover pan with foil and seal.
Bake about 2 hours at 325°. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage approximately 15 minutes (do not overcook); drain.
Put half the cabbage into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle half the salt, pepper, sugar and flour, then add half the cheese and margarine.
Repeat layers.
Top with hot milk.
Last, cover with stuffing mix.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until topping is well browned.
Yields approximately 6 servings.

title: chicken mole
directions: Cut up chicken into small pieces; boil in water with salt, garlic and onions.
When the chicken is cooked, remove 3 to 4 cups (8 ounces) of broth.
Stir the mole thoroughly.
In a pan stir/blend in the mole and 2 tablespoons of oil.
On low heat, cook/simmer the mole.
Mix the mole and allow it to simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix together and spread between layers.
Reserve a small portion and add to a small carton of Cool Whip; spread this on top and sides.
Keep in refrigerator.
Wait 3 days before eating.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost with 1 (10 ounce) package berries and 1 quart Cool Whip.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add in pumpkin and spices until well mixed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip.

title: old fashioned honey cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix liquid ingredients.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in a well-greased tube pan.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed, split.
Mix together sugar, sour cream and coconut and reserve 1 cup.
Frost each layer with the mixture.
Mix reserved 1 cup mixture with Cool Whip.
Frost with mixture.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix together well.
Serve with corn chips or as a salad dressing.

title: tortilla-spanish omelet(tor-tee-ya)
directions: You will need a Teflon frypan, medium or large size.

title: carrot salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the carrots, onion and green pepper.
In another bowl, thoroughly mix together the additional ingredients to make a dressing.
Pour over the vegetables and marinate for 24 hours, stirring once.
Serve cold.
Keeps well.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine
potatoes,
sugar,
eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup butter and pecans together and sprinkle on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well together, except soup or barbecue sauce.
Brown in small amount of vegetable oil.
Drain.
Cover with soup or barbecue sauce.

title: french-style string beans and tomatoes
directions: Cook bacon and set aside.
Saute onion in bacon drippings. Drain.
Drain green beans and add tomatoes in 2-quart pan on medium heat.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and onion and cook 15 minutes.
When ready to serve, add crumbled bacon.

title: stir-fry cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Heat oil in skillet 2 to 3 minutes. Brown chicken and drain on paper towels.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons oil to skillet.
Add green beans and yams.
Cook for 2 minutes. Then add chicken, water chestnuts and stir-fry mix.
Cook until thick (about 10 minutes).
Stir in water and cashews.
Cook another 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: bachelor's roast
directions: Score roast; season with 1/2 teaspoon each of salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Sear roast in pan in oil on all sides until browned. Remove from pan and place in foil-lined roasting pan.
Pour Coca-Cola and catsup over roast.
Cover loosely with foil and bake for 3 hours at 325°.

title: green pepper steak
directions: With a sharp knife, cut beef across grain in narrow strips 1/8 or 1/2-inch.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef. Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables (pepper, onion and celery).

title: quick supper casserole
directions: Spray a large baking dish with Pam.
Place pork chops or chicken in pan.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Cook at 325° for about 25 minutes.
Prepare instant rice.
Remove meat from oven and add rice and frozen vegetables (that have been cooked in water and drained).
Return to oven for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: meat muffins
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix beef with barbecue sauce, onion, brown sugar and salt.
Open biscuits and press each into the cup of a muffin pan, making sure the dough goes up the sides of the cup.
Spoon meat mixture into biscuit cups and sprinkle the top with 3/4 cup of cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chinese chews
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour, sifted with salt.
Stir in vanilla, nuts and dates.
Spread in greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Cut into bars and sift confectioners sugar over all.

title: cheddar puff
directions: Butter well a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and heat oven to 350°. In bowl of electric mixer beat eggs until light.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, shredded cheese and melted butter; beat until well blended.
Stir in diced ham.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until top is golden and center is set.
Minced or diced mushrooms or diced shrimp may replace ham. May be assembled and baked later.
Reheats well covered.
May cut into small squares for hors d'oeuvres.
Serves 12 to 16 as main course for brunch.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cream the potatoes and sugar until smooth. Add margarine (melted), eggs and rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° until almost firm, about 30 minutes. Remove to add topping.
Return and continue cooking until done.

title: 8-layer jello mold salad
directions: Oil 3-quart baking dish.
Dissolve 1 package jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool 15 minutes in refrigerator.
Add 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Pour into baking dish.
Set 1 1/2 hours.
Next, mix same flavor jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour onto first layer.
Set 1 1/2 hours.
Repeat these steps until all jello is used.

title: colby cheese potatoes
directions: Layer ingredients in a casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Cook the chocolate pudding.
Then mix with a dry package of devil's food cake mix in a bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Top with chocolate chips and slivered almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients 20 minutes.
Chop celery, pepper and onion.
Put in macaroni for last minute of cooking.
Drain well.
